{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012VB6qhV2G6n9CcDUSF7AKz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{\n     2→  \"project\": \"MediaTrackerPlus\",\n     3→  \"branchName\": \"ralph/content-list-facets\",\n     4→  \"description\": \"Content List Facets -- Multi-dimensional facet filter panel for content list pages with 6 filter dimensions, mobile-first responsive design, and URL-persisted state\",\n     5→  \"jiraEpicKey\": null,\n     6→  \"userStories\": [\n     7→    {\n     8→      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n     9→      \"title\": \"Install @radix-ui/react-slider and @radix-ui/react-collapsible\",\n    10→      \"description\": \"As a setup agent, I need to install the required UI primitive packages before any frontend component work begins.\",\n    11→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    12→        \"@radix-ui/react-slider is added to client/package.json dependencies\",\n    13→        \"@radix-ui/react-collapsible is added to client/package.json dependencies\",\n    14→        \"npm install completes without errors from the project root\",\n    15→        \"Both packages resolve correctly (no peer dependency conflicts with React 17)\",\n    16→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n    17→        \"Tests pass\"\n    18→      ],\n    19→      \"priority\": 1,\n    20→      \"passes\": true,\n    21→      \"notes\": \"Prerequisite for year/rating range sliders and collapsible accordion sections. Both packages declare react ^16.8 || ^17.0 || ^18.0 || ^19.0 as peer deps -- React 17 is supported.\",\n    22→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n    23→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    24→    },\n    25→    {\n    26→      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n    27→      \"title\": \"Add creator column for TV shows (schema + metadata mapping)\",\n    28→      \"description\": \"As a database agent, I need to add a creator column to the mediaItem table and map TMDB's created_by field so the creator facet works for TV content.\",\n    29→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    30→        \"New migration adds a `creator` column (STRING, nullable) to the mediaItem table\",\n    31→        \"`creator` added to MediaItemBase as `creator?: string` in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n    32→        \"`creator` added to `mediaItemColumns` array in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n    33→        \"`mapTvShow()` in /server/src/metadata/provider/tmdb.ts maps `item.created_by?.map(c => c.name).join(', ')` to `tvShow.creator`\",\n    34→        \"creator is stored as a plain string (same pattern as developer, not a CSV array)\",\n    35→        \"Existing TV items are not backfilled (populate on next metadata refresh)\",\n    36→        \"Unit tests verify: migration applies cleanly, mapTvShow populates creator from created_by array\",\n    37→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n    38→        \"Tests pass\"\n    39→      ],\n    40→      \"priority\": 2,\n    41→      \"passes\": true,\n    42→      \"notes\": \"TMDB already fetches created_by in TvDetailsResponse but discards it in mapTvShow(). This is a one-line mapping addition plus migration.\",\n    43→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n    44→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    45→    },\n    46→    {\n    47→      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n    48→      \"title\": \"Add director column for movies (schema + metadata mapping)\",\n    49→      \"description\": \"As a database agent, I need to add a director column to the mediaItem table and extend the TMDB movie details call to include credits so the creator facet works for movie content.\",\n    50→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    51→        \"New migration adds a `director` column (STRING, nullable) to the mediaItem table\",\n    52→        \"`director` added to MediaItemBase as `director?: string` and to `mediaItemColumns` in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n    53→        \"TMDbMovie.details() call in /server/src/metadata/provider/tmdb.ts includes `append_to_response: 'credits'` in the request params\",\n    54→        \"TMDbApi.MovieDetailsResponse type extended with `credits?: { crew: TMDbApi.Crew[] }`\",\n    55→        \"`mapMovie()` maps `item.credits?.crew?.filter(c => c.job === 'Director').map(c => c.name).join(', ')` to `movie.director`\",\n    56→        \"director is stored as a plain string (may contain comma-separated names for co-directed films)\",\n    57→        \"Existing movie items are not backfilled (populate on next metadata refresh)\",\n    58→        \"Unit tests verify: migration applies cleanly, mapMovie extracts directors from credits crew where job === 'Director'\",\n    59→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n    60→        \"Tests pass\"\n    61→      ],\n    62→      \"priority\": 3,\n    63→      \"passes\": true,\n    64→      \"notes\": \"The Crew type is already defined in tmdb.ts (~lines 457-469). The details call needs append_to_response=credits added to the existing request params.\",\n    65→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n    66→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    67→    },\n    68→    {\n    69→      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n    70→      \"title\": \"Add publisher column for games (schema + metadata mapping)\",\n    71→      \"description\": \"As a database agent, I need to add a publisher column to the mediaItem table and map IGDB's involved_companies publisher entries so the publisher facet works for video game content.\",\n    72→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    73→        \"New migration adds a `publisher` column (STRING, nullable) to the mediaItem table\",\n    74→        \"`publisher` added to MediaItemBase as `publisher?: string` and to `mediaItemColumns` in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n    75→        \"`mapGame()` in /server/src/metadata/provider/igdb.ts maps publisher names from `involved_companies` entries where `publisher === true`; multiple publishers joined with ', '\",\n    76→        \"publisher is stored as a plain string (same pattern as developer, not a CSV array)\",\n    77→        \"Existing game items are not backfilled (populate on next metadata refresh)\",\n    78→        \"Unit tests verify: migration applies cleanly, mapGame extracts publishers from involved_companies where publisher flag is true\",\n    79→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n    80→        \"Tests pass\"\n    81→      ],\n    82→      \"priority\": 4,\n    83→      \"passes\": true,\n    84→      \"notes\": \"The involved_companies data is already fetched by the IGDB provider for the developer field. Filter entries by publisher === true, map to names, join with ', '.\",\n    85→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n    86→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    87→    },\n    88→    {\n    89→      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n    90→      \"title\": \"Create creator field normalization and splitting utilities\",\n    91→      \"description\": \"As a backend utility agent, I need shared utilities for normalizing and splitting creator CSV fields so all facet aggregation and deserialization produces clean, deduplicated tokens.\",\n    92→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    93→        \"`normalizeCreatorField(names: string[]): string[]` exists in /server/src/utils/normalizeCreators.ts -- trims whitespace from each name, filters empty strings, deduplicates while preserving order\",\n    94→        \"normalizeCreatorField is applied before join(',') in OpenLibrary mapBook(), Audible mapAudiobook(), and the Goodreads import controller\",\n    95→        \"`splitCreatorField(csv: string | null): string[]` splits stored CSV on ',' and trims each token, filtering empty results\",\n    96→        \"splitCreatorField replaces raw .split(',') in: mediaItem.ts deserialization, items.ts mapRawResult, and details.ts deserialization\",\n    97→        \"Unit tests cover: multiple authors, single author, empty string, null, names with leading/trailing whitespace, confirmed 'First Last' format preserved\",\n    98→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n    99→        \"Tests pass\"\n   100→      ],\n   101→      \"priority\": 5,\n   102→      \"passes\": true,\n   103→      \"notes\": \"All name sources confirmed 'First Last' format -- no Last,First conversion needed. Normalization is defensive trimming and dedup only. splitCreatorField handles the leading-space problem from join(', ') storage pattern.\",\n   104→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   105→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   106→    },\n   107→    {\n   108→      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n   109→      \"title\": \"Add multi-facet filter params to paginated items endpoint\",\n   110→      \"description\": \"As a backend API agent, I need the paginated items endpoint to accept multi-value and range facet parameters so the frontend can fetch filtered result sets across all 6 dimensions plus media type and status.\",\n   111→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   112→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `genres` param as comma-separated string (e.g., genres=Action,Comedy)\",\n   113→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `languages` param as comma-separated string\",\n   114→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `creators` param as comma-separated string\",\n   115→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `publishers` param as comma-separated string\",\n   116→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `mediaTypes` param as comma-separated string filtering to matching media types\",\n   117→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `yearMin` and `yearMax` as integer params filtering by releaseDate year\",\n   118→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `ratingMin` and `ratingMax` as float params (0-10) filtering by tmdbRating\",\n   119→        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `status` param as comma-separated keys (rated,unrated,watchlist,seen) mapping to existing boolean flags: rated -> onlyWithUserRating, unrated -> onlyWithoutUserRating, watchlist -> onlyOnWatchlist, seen -> onlySeenItems\",\n   120→        \"Multi-value genres, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes apply OR logic within each dimension\",\n   121→        \"All active dimensions combine with AND logic (e.g., genres=Action AND language=en)\",\n   122→        \"yearMin/yearMax and ratingMin/ratingMax apply as inclusive bounds\",\n   123→        \"Items with no tmdbRating excluded when ratingMin > 0\",\n   124→        \"Knex query uses LIKE '%genre%' per selected genre (OR-chained orWhere) -- genres column is CSV, not JSON\",\n   125→        \"publishers filter uses exact equality check against publisher column (plain string, not CSV)\",\n   126→        \"All new params are optional; omitting them does not change existing behavior\",\n   127→        \"Existing singular `genre` param continues to work independently alongside plural `genres`\",\n   128→        \"Legacy `filter` param continues to work when `status` param is absent\",\n   129→        \"Unit tests verify: each filter param independently, combined filters with AND/OR logic, empty/absent params return all results, backward compat with existing genre and filter params\",\n   130→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   131→        \"Tests pass\"\n   132→      ],\n   133→      \"priority\": 6,\n   134→      \"passes\": true,\n   135→      \"notes\": \"Follow the existing single-value genre LIKE pattern for the plural genres param. The existing `year` URL param filters by seen-date year (not releaseDate) -- do not conflict with yearMin/yearMax. Add yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, genres, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes, status as new optional fields on GetItemsArgs.\",\n   136→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   137→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   138→    },\n   139→    {\n   140→      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n   141→      \"title\": \"Create facet counts API endpoint\",\n   142→      \"description\": \"As a backend API architect agent, I need to design and implement the facet counts endpoint that returns available facet options with item counts across all dimensions, scoped to the current user's library. This is the most architecturally complex backend story -- leverage the software-architect agent for query design if the aggregation logic is unclear.\",\n   143→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   144→        \"GET /api/items/facets endpoint exists on ItemsController and returns { genres, years, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes } each as Array<{ value: string; count: number }>\",\n   145→        \"Endpoint accepts optional mediaType query param; when provided, scopes to that type and omits mediaTypes; when absent, aggregates all types and includes mediaTypes\",\n   146→        \"Endpoint accepts same filter params as GET /api/items/paginated (genres, languages, creators, publishers, yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, status, search, filter) so counts reflect currently filtered set\",\n   147→        \"Each dimension sorted by count descending\",\n   148→        \"Options with zero counts excluded from response\",\n   149→        \"years dimension returns individual year values derived from releaseDate\",\n   150→        \"creators dimension aggregates from director (movies), creator (TV), authors (books/audiobooks), developer (games) using splitCreatorField(); on mixed-content (no mediaType) unions all four into single list\",\n   151→        \"publishers dimension populated from publisher column; included when mediaType=video_game or when no mediaType; hidden for other single-type pages\",\n   152→        \"Genres aggregation uses application-layer splitting (fetch rows, split in TypeScript) -- NOT json_each() -- because genres column is CSV\",\n   153→        \"Facets query scopes to current user's library by joining same listItem/seen subqueries used by getItemsKnexSql -- does NOT query raw mediaItem table\",\n   154→        \"Run `npm run build:routes` after adding getFacets to ItemsController -- verify client typed API method is generated in rest-api/index.ts\",\n   155→        \"Unit tests verify: response shape, mediaType scoping, count accuracy, zero-count exclusion, user-scoping prevents cross-user data leakage\",\n   156→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   157→        \"Tests pass\"\n   158→      ],\n   159→      \"priority\": 7,\n   160→      \"passes\": true,\n   161→      \"notes\": \"Most complex backend story. The query must mirror getItemsKnexSql's user-scoping joins. Genre splitting must happen in TS application layer, not SQL, because genres is a CSV column. The server uses typescript-routes-to-openapi -- build:routes regenerates routes.ts and rest-api/index.ts.\",\n   162→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   163→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"HIGH\"\n   164→    },\n   165→    {\n   166→      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n   167→      \"title\": \"Create useFacets hook and useMultiValueSearchParam\",\n   168→      \"description\": \"As a frontend infrastructure agent, I need to create the core state management hooks that read/write all facet URL params with a merge strategy that preserves existing params, providing setter functions and derived state for the entire facet feature.\",\n   169→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   170→        \"`useMultiValueSearchParam` hook created in /client/src/hooks/ -- reads/writes comma-separated multi-value URL params for genres, languages, creators, publishers, status, mediaTypes\",\n   171→        \"`useFacets()` hook created in /client/src/hooks/facets.ts as single source of truth for all facet URL state\",\n   172→        \"useFacets reads/writes: genres, yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, languages, creators, publishers, status, mediaTypes\",\n   173→        \"useFacets returns: active facet query params object (for API calls), activeFacetCount number, and individual setter functions per dimension including setPublishers and setMediaTypes\",\n   174→        \"All setter functions use merge strategy -- spread all existing searchParams before writing new value; never call setSearchParams with bare object\",\n   175→        \"orderBy and sortOrder URL params are explicitly preserved by all facet setters (never dropped)\",\n   176→        \"Any facet change resets pagination to page 1 via the existing handleArgumentChange callback pattern\",\n   177→        \"useFacets does NOT own orderBy or sortOrder -- those remain managed exclusively by useOrderByComponent\",\n   178→        \"Unit tests verify: param read/write round-trip, merge strategy preserves all existing params including orderBy/sortOrder, pagination resets on facet change, activeFacetCount accuracy\",\n   179→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   180→        \"Tests pass\"\n   181→      ],\n   182→      \"priority\": 8,\n   183→      \"passes\": true,\n   184→      \"notes\": \"Separate from existing scalar useUpdateSearchParams to avoid breaking OrderBy, pagination, and useMenuComponent. useFacets is the foundation for all frontend facet components. useFilterBy hook is no longer called when showFacets={true}.\",\n   185→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   186→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   187→    },\n   188→    {\n   189→      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n   190→      \"title\": \"Create FacetPanel desktop sidebar layout with accordion structure\",\n   191→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to build the FacetPanel container with collapsible accordion sections, the FacetSection wrapper, and the shared ExpandableList component -- rendering as a persistent 240px sidebar on desktop.\",\n   192→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   193→        \"FacetPanel component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetPanel.tsx\",\n   194→        \"FacetSection component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetSection.tsx using @radix-ui/react-collapsible for keyboard nav and ARIA\",\n   195→        \"ExpandableList component created in /client/src/components/Facets/ExpandableList.tsx -- shared 15-item truncation with 'Show more / Show less' toggle\",\n   196→        \"FacetPanel renders as 240px fixed-width sidebar beside the grid on screens >= 1024px (flex layout: sidebar + grid in a row)\",\n   197→        \"Sidebar is always visible on desktop; no button required to open\",\n   198→        \"Each facet dimension renders as a collapsible FacetSection with chevron toggle\",\n   199→        \"Chevron rotates 180 degrees when expanded (CSS transform, no JS animation)\",\n   200→        \"Sections start collapsed; auto-expand when they have active selections\",\n   201→        \"'Clear all filters' button appears at top of panel only when at least one facet is active\",\n   202→        \"Clicking 'Clear all' resets all facet URL params via useFacets and collapses all sections\",\n   203→        \"Uses existing TailwindCSS dark theme and accent color for checked/active states\",\n   204→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   205→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   206→        \"Tests pass\",\n   207→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   208→      ],\n   209→      \"priority\": 9,\n   210→      \"passes\": true,\n   211→      \"notes\": \"Creates the shell component structure. Individual facet section content (genre, year, etc.) will be added by subsequent stories. The grid area shrinks to accommodate the sidebar on desktop.\",\n   212→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   213→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   214→    },\n   215→    {\n   216→      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n   217→      \"title\": \"Create FacetPanel mobile bottom drawer\",\n   218→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the mobile-responsive variant of the FacetPanel as a bottom sheet drawer that opens from a toolbar Filters button, with live grid updates on selection.\",\n   219→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   220→        \"On screens < 1024px, FacetPanel sidebar is hidden\",\n   221→        \"A 'Filters' button renders in the list toolbar area near existing OrderBy controls\",\n   222→        \"Filters button visually matches existing OrderBy button style\",\n   223→        \"When any facet is active, Filters button shows a badge with count of active facet dimensions\",\n   224→        \"Tapping Filters opens a bottom sheet drawer with full FacetPanel content\",\n   225→        \"Drawer uses position:fixed bottom:0 left:0 right:0 with high z-index\",\n   226→        \"Drawer mounted via existing Portal component (/client/src/components/Portal.tsx)\",\n   227→        \"Drawer has visible 'Close' button at top and closes on backdrop tap\",\n   228→        \"Selecting a facet inside drawer immediately updates background grid (no 'Apply' button needed)\",\n   229→        \"Drawer is scrollable if facet content exceeds viewport height\",\n   230→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   231→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   232→        \"Tests pass\",\n   233→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   234→      ],\n   235→      \"priority\": 10,\n   236→      \"passes\": true,\n   237→      \"notes\": \"No animated transitions required (functional behavior only; enhancement deferred). FacetPanel content inside drawer is the same accordion structure as the desktop sidebar.\",\n   238→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   239→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   240→    },\n   241→    {\n   242→      \"id\": \"US-011\",\n   243→      \"title\": \"Implement genre facet section with multi-select checkboxes\",\n   244→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the genre facet accordion section with the shared FacetCheckboxList component, count badges, and expandable list so users can filter by one or more genres.\",\n   245→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   246→        \"FacetCheckboxList component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetCheckboxList.tsx reusing existing Checkbox from /client/src/components/Checkbox.tsx\",\n   247→        \"Genre FacetSection lists up to 15 genres as checkbox items with count badges using ExpandableList\",\n   248→        \"Genres sorted by count descending\",\n   249→        \"'Show more' link expands to all genres; 'Show less' collapses back to 15\",\n   250→        \"Multiple genres can be checked simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n   251→        \"Checked items are visually distinct (filled checkbox + accent color)\",\n   252→        \"Count badges update reactively when other facets change (React Query refetch on param change)\",\n   253→        \"Selecting a genre updates URL param genres as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n   254→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   255→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   256→        \"Tests pass\",\n   257→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   258→      ],\n   259→      \"priority\": 11,\n   260→      \"passes\": true,\n   261→      \"notes\": \"FacetCheckboxList is a shared component reused by genre, language, creator, and publisher sections. Reuses existing Checkbox from /client/src/components/Checkbox.tsx for consistent styling.\",\n   262→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   263→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   264→    },\n   265→    {\n   266→      \"id\": \"US-012\",\n   267→      \"title\": \"Implement year range facet section with dual-handle slider\",\n   268→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the release year range facet with a dual-handle slider and paired numeric inputs using @radix-ui/react-slider so users can filter content by era.\",\n   269→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   270→        \"FacetRangeSlider component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetRangeSlider.tsx using @radix-ui/react-slider\",\n   271→        \"Year FacetSection shows dual-handle range slider spanning from earliest available year to current year\",\n   272→        \"Two numeric inputs below slider show current yearMin and yearMax values\",\n   273→        \"Dragging either handle updates corresponding numeric input in real-time (onValueChange)\",\n   274→        \"Typing into numeric input updates slider on blur\",\n   275→        \"URL params yearMin and yearMax written on slider release (onValueCommit), not on every drag step\",\n   276→        \"Input values clamped to available year range; invalid inputs revert to nearest valid value\",\n   277→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   278→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   279→        \"Tests pass\",\n   280→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   281→      ],\n   282→      \"priority\": 12,\n   283→      \"passes\": true,\n   284→      \"notes\": \"FacetRangeSlider is a shared component reused by the rating range facet (US-013). Uses @radix-ui/react-slider for accessible dual-handle range with TailwindCSS styling.\",\n   285→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   286→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   287→    },\n   288→    {\n   289→      \"id\": \"US-013\",\n   290→      \"title\": \"Implement rating range facet section with 0.5-step slider\",\n   291→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the TMDB rating range facet section reusing the FacetRangeSlider with a 0-10 range and 0.5-step increments.\",\n   292→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   293→        \"Rating FacetSection shows dual-handle range slider from 0 to 10 with 0.5-step increments\",\n   294→        \"Two numeric inputs show current ratingMin and ratingMax (e.g., '6.5' - '10.0')\",\n   295→        \"Dragging either handle updates its numeric input in real-time\",\n   296→        \"Typing into numeric input updates slider on blur; values clamped to 0-10\",\n   297→        \"URL params ratingMin and ratingMax written on slider release\",\n   298→        \"Reuses FacetRangeSlider component from US-012 with different min/max/step config\",\n   299→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   300→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   301→        \"Tests pass\",\n   302→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   303→      ],\n   304→      \"priority\": 13,\n   305→      \"passes\": true,\n   306→      \"notes\": \"Reuses FacetRangeSlider from US-012 with rating-specific props: min=0, max=10, step=0.5. Backend excludes items with no tmdbRating when ratingMin > 0 (already handled in US-006).\",\n   307→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   308→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n   309→    },\n   310→    {\n   311→      \"id\": \"US-014\",\n   312→      \"title\": \"Implement language facet section with Intl.DisplayNames mapping\",\n   313→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the language facet section with checkbox list and browser-native language code-to-name mapping using Intl.DisplayNames for zero-bundle-size locale resolution.\",\n   314→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   315→        \"Language FacetSection lists available languages as checkbox items with count badges using FacetCheckboxList\",\n   316→        \"Language codes mapped to display names using browser Intl.DisplayNames API (e.g., en -> 'English', fr -> 'French')\",\n   317→        \"Multiple languages can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n   318→        \"Selecting a language updates URL param languages as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n   319→        \"Section is hidden when only one language is present in facet data (no filtering value)\",\n   320→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   321→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   322→        \"Tests pass\",\n   323→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   324→      ],\n   325→      \"priority\": 14,\n   326→      \"passes\": true,\n   327→      \"notes\": \"Uses Intl.DisplayNames for zero-bundle-size locale name resolution instead of a hardcoded mapping table. Reuses FacetCheckboxList from US-011.\",\n   328→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   329→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n   330→    },\n   331→    {\n   332→      \"id\": \"US-015\",\n   333→      \"title\": \"Implement creator facet section with context-aware labels\",\n   334→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the creator facet section with media-type-aware labels (Director/Creator/Author/Developer) so users can browse a specific person's body of work across all content types.\",\n   335→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   336→        \"Creator FacetSection renders with context-aware label: 'Director' for movies, 'Creator' for TV, 'Author' for books and audiobooks, 'Developer' for games, generic 'Creator' on mixed-content pages\",\n   337→        \"Section hidden when current media type has no creator data in facet response\",\n   338→        \"Checkbox list with count badges using FacetCheckboxList and ExpandableList (up to 15, Show more/less)\",\n   339→        \"Multiple creators can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n   340→        \"Selecting a creator updates URL param creators as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n   341→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   342→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   343→        \"Tests pass\",\n   344→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   345→      ],\n   346→      \"priority\": 15,\n   347→      \"passes\": true,\n   348→      \"notes\": \"Label mapping depends on the mediaType prop passed to FacetPanel. On mixed-content pages (no mediaType), backend returns a union of all creator fields and the generic 'Creator' label is used.\",\n   349→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   350→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   351→    },\n   352→    {\n   353→      \"id\": \"US-016\",\n   354→      \"title\": \"Implement status facet section (replaces FilterByComponent)\",\n   355→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the status facet section that absorbs the existing FilterBy dropdown functionality into the facet panel, with media-type-aware seen labels and AND logic between selections.\",\n   356→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   357→        \"Status FacetSection renders checkboxes: 'Rated', 'Unrated', 'On watchlist', and a media-type-aware seen label ('Watched' for movies/TV, 'Played' for games, 'Read' for books, 'Listened' for audiobooks)\",\n   358→        \"Multiple status values can be checked simultaneously (AND logic -- item must match all)\",\n   359→        \"Selecting statuses updates URL param status as comma-separated keys (e.g., status=rated,watchlist)\",\n   360→        \"Internal keys: rated, unrated, watchlist, seen\",\n   361→        \"When showFacets={true}, FilterByComponent is NOT rendered in the toolbar -- Status facet replaces it entirely\",\n   362→        \"When showFacets={false} (e.g., statistics pages), FilterByComponent continues to render unchanged -- no regression\",\n   363→        \"Legacy filter URL param preserved for backward compatibility: if filter present and status absent, backend treats as before\",\n   364→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   365→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   366→        \"Tests pass\",\n   367→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   368→      ],\n   369→      \"priority\": 16,\n   370→      \"passes\": true,\n   371→      \"notes\": \"Backend mapping (rated -> onlyWithUserRating, etc.) already implemented in US-006. This story is frontend-only: Status accordion section + FilterByComponent suppression when showFacets={true}.\",\n   372→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   373→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   374→    },\n   375→    {\n   376→      \"id\": \"US-017\",\n   377→      \"title\": \"Implement publisher facet section (games and mixed-content)\",\n   378→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the publisher facet section that renders only for video games or mixed-content pages where game publisher data exists.\",\n   379→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   380→        \"Publisher FacetSection renders only when mediaType=video_game or on mixed-content pages where at least one publisher value exists in facet data\",\n   381→        \"Section NOT rendered on movies, TV, books, or audiobooks single-type pages\",\n   382→        \"Section header reads 'Publisher'\",\n   383→        \"Checkbox list with count badges using FacetCheckboxList and ExpandableList (up to 15, Show more/less)\",\n   384→        \"Publishers sorted by count descending\",\n   385→        \"Multiple publishers can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n   386→        \"Selecting a publisher updates URL param publishers as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n   387→        \"Count badges update reactively when other facets change\",\n   388→        \"Section hidden when no publisher data present (all games added before next metadata refresh)\",\n   389→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   390→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   391→        \"Tests pass\",\n   392→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   393→      ],\n   394→      \"priority\": 17,\n   395→      \"passes\": false,\n   396→      \"notes\": \"Visibility logic: check if facet response publishers array has any entries. Reuses FacetCheckboxList and ExpandableList from previous stories.\",\n   397→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   398→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n   399→    },\n   400→    {\n   401→      \"id\": \"US-018\",\n   402→      \"title\": \"Implement Media Type facet section (mixed-content pages)\",\n   403→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the Media Type facet section that renders only on mixed-content pages (Watchlist, Upcoming, In Progress) so users can narrow results by movie/TV/game/book/audiobook.\",\n   404→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   405→        \"Media Type FacetSection renders on mixed-content pages (WatchlistPage, UpcomingPage, InProgressPage) when facets enabled\",\n   406→        \"Section NOT rendered on single-type pages (ItemsPage -- already scoped to one type)\",\n   407→        \"Each media type present in user's library shown as checkbox with display label and count (e.g., 'Movie (42)', 'TV Show (18)')\",\n   408→        \"Display labels use existing media type label mapping in codebase (not raw enum values like video_game)\",\n   409→        \"Multiple types can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n   410→        \"Selecting types updates URL param mediaTypes (comma-separated, e.g., mediaTypes=movie,tv) and resets page to 1\",\n   411→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   412→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   413→        \"Tests pass\",\n   414→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   415→      ],\n   416→      \"priority\": 18,\n   417→      \"passes\": false,\n   418→      \"notes\": \"Backend mediaTypes filter already added in US-006. This story is frontend-only. Uses FacetCheckboxList for consistent checkbox styling.\",\n   419→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   420→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   421→    },\n   422→    {\n   423→      \"id\": \"US-019\",\n   424→      \"title\": \"Implement active facet chips row with individual dismissal\",\n   425→      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to create the ActiveFacetChips component that displays all active filter selections as removable chips above the grid, with horizontal scrolling on mobile.\",\n   426→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   427→        \"ActiveFacetChips component created in /client/src/components/Facets/ActiveFacetChips.tsx\",\n   428→        \"Horizontal row of chips renders between toolbar and grid when at least one facet is active\",\n   429→        \"Each chip shows dimension label and value (e.g., 'Genre: Action', 'Year: 2010-2020', 'Rating: 7-10')\",\n   430→        \"Year and rating ranges each produce a single chip showing the range (not individual chips per bound)\",\n   431→        \"Clicking x on a chip removes that specific facet selection, updates URL params, and resets page to 1\",\n   432→        \"'Clear all' button at end of chip row resets all facets and URL params\",\n   433→        \"Chip row hidden when no facets are active (no empty space left behind)\",\n   434→        \"On mobile, chip row uses horizontally scrollable container to avoid wrapping\",\n   435→        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n   436→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   437→        \"Tests pass\",\n   438→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   439→      ],\n   440→      \"priority\": 19,\n   441→      \"passes\": false,\n   442→      \"notes\": \"Reads from useFacets to determine active selections. Calls individual setter functions from useFacets to remove specific selections on chip dismiss.\",\n   443→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   444→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   445→    },\n   446→    {\n   447→      \"id\": \"US-020\",\n   448→      \"title\": \"Verify sort order compatibility with active facets\",\n   449→      \"description\": \"As a QA agent, I need to verify and ensure that the existing OrderByComponent and all 10 sort fields remain fully functional when facets are active, and that facet interactions never drop or reset sort params.\",\n   450→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   451→        \"OrderByComponent continues to render in PaginatedGridItems toolbar when showFacets={true} -- it is NOT removed or relocated\",\n   452→        \"On mobile, sort direction toggle button and sort field menu remain accessible alongside Filters button\",\n   453→        \"All 10 MediaItemOrderBy sort fields (title, releaseDate, lastSeen, status, mediaType, progress, recommended, nextAiring, lastAiring, unseenEpisodes) work when facets are active\",\n   454→        \"Both SortOrder directions (asc, desc) work correctly with any active facet selection\",\n   455→        \"orderBy and sortOrder URL params are preserved by all useFacets setter functions -- never dropped\",\n   456→        \"Changing a facet does NOT reset orderBy or sortOrder to their defaults\",\n   457→        \"Any sort change still resets pagination to page 1 (existing behavior preserved, not broken)\",\n   458→        \"Unit tests verify: facet setter preserves orderBy/sortOrder params, sort change with active facets returns correctly ordered results\",\n   459→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   460→        \"Tests pass\",\n   461→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   462→      ],\n   463→      \"priority\": 20,\n   464→      \"passes\": false,\n   465→      \"notes\": \"No changes to OrderBy.tsx or useOrderByComponent are required. The merge requirement is enforced at the useFacets setter level only. useOrderByComponent already uses its own merge strategy via useUpdateSearchParams.\",\n   466→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   467→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   468→    },\n   469→    {\n   470→      \"id\": \"US-021\",\n   471→      \"title\": \"Integrate FacetPanel into PaginatedGridItems and enable on content pages\",\n   472→      \"description\": \"As an integration agent, I need to wire the completed FacetPanel, ActiveFacetChips, and all facet sections into PaginatedGridItems via the showFacets prop, enable it on ItemsPage/WatchlistPage/UpcomingPage/InProgressPage, set up parallel API queries, and implement cross-type navigation param forwarding.\",\n   473→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   474→        \"PaginatedGridItems accepts new optional showFacets?: boolean prop\",\n   475→        \"When showFacets={true}, PaginatedGridItems renders FacetPanel alongside grid (desktop sidebar layout + mobile drawer)\",\n   476→        \"When showFacets={true}, ActiveFacetChips row renders between toolbar and grid\",\n   477→        \"When showFacets={true}, FilterByComponent is NOT rendered in toolbar (Status facet replaces it)\",\n   478→        \"/api/items/facets and /api/items/paginated called in parallel (two separate useQuery calls) on facet param change\",\n   479→        \"keepPreviousData: true applied to both queries to prevent flash of empty state during refetch\",\n   480→        \"staleTime: 30000 applied to facets query only; items query always re-fetches on param change\",\n   481→        \"ItemsPage passes showFacets={true} to PaginatedGridItems\",\n   482→        \"WatchlistPage passes showFacets={true} to PaginatedGridItems\",\n   483→        \"UpcomingPage and InProgressPage pass showFacets={true} if they use PaginatedGridItems; deferred with follow-up ticket if they don't\",\n   484→        \"On mixed-content pages (Watchlist, Upcoming, In Progress), useFacets passes no mediaType to facets API; Media Type section renders; creator section shows union labeled 'Creator'\",\n   485→        \"Nav links between single-type pages (/movies, /tv, /games, /books, /audiobooks) carry forward: genres, yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, languages, orderBy, sortOrder\",\n   486→        \"Nav links between single-type pages DROP: creators, publishers, status on cross-type navigation (creators field source changes, publishers is games-specific, status labels change per type)\",\n   487→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   488→        \"Tests pass\",\n   489→        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n   490→      ],\n   491→      \"priority\": 21,\n   492→      \"passes\": false,\n   493→      \"notes\": \"This is the final wiring story that brings all facet components together. All individual components (US-009 through US-019) must be complete. The grid area shrinks to accommodate the sidebar on desktop via flex layout.\",\n   494→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   495→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n   496→    },\n   497→    {\n   498→      \"id\": \"US-022\",\n   499→      \"title\": \"Extract and compile i18n translations for all 28 language files\",\n   500→      \"description\": \"As an i18n agent, I need to extract all new translatable strings introduced by the facet feature and add translation entries to all 28 language catalog files so the feature is fully internationalized.\",\n   501→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   502→        \"All new user-facing strings in /client/src/components/Facets/ are wrapped with @lingui/macro t() or <Trans> -- verify no unwrapped raw strings\",\n   503→        \"Run lingui extract to pull new message entries into catalog files\",\n   504→        \"All 28 language catalog files updated with new translation keys for: dimension labels (Genre, Year, Rating, Language, Director, Creator, Author, Developer, Publisher, Media Type, Status), button text (Filters, Clear all, Show more, Show less, Close), chip labels, status options (Rated, Unrated, On watchlist, Watched, Played, Read, Listened)\",\n   505→        \"English translations are complete and accurate\",\n   506→        \"Non-English translations use English string as placeholder (matching project convention for new keys)\",\n   507→        \"No existing translations modified or removed\",\n   508→        \"lingui compile runs without errors\",\n   509→        \"Typecheck passes\",\n   510→        \"Tests pass\"\n   511→      ],\n   512→      \"priority\": 22,\n   513→      \"passes\": false,\n   514→      \"notes\": \"Run `lingui extract` then `lingui compile` from the client directory. Check project convention for placeholder translations in non-English files.\",\n   515→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   516→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n   517→    },\n   518→    {\n   519→      \"id\": \"US-023\",\n   520→      \"title\": \"Integration tests for Content List Facets feature\",\n   521→      \"description\": \"As a QA agent, I need comprehensive integration tests that verify all product requirements end-to-end, covering the complete user journey from facet selection through grid filtering across all media types, page contexts, responsive layouts, and URL persistence.\",\n   522→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   523→        \"Integration test: User applies genre facet on movies page -- grid shows only matching movies, chip appears, count badges update\",\n   524→        \"Integration test: User applies multiple facets simultaneously (genre + year range + language) -- AND logic between dimensions, OR within genre dimension\",\n   525→        \"Integration test: Year range slider updates URL params on release and grid filters correctly by releaseDate year\",\n   526→        \"Integration test: Rating range slider excludes items with no tmdbRating when ratingMin > 0\",\n   527→        \"Integration test: Creator facet shows 'Director' label on movies page, 'Author' on books page, generic 'Creator' on watchlist (mixed-content)\",\n   528→        \"Integration test: Publisher facet renders on games page and mixed-content pages, hidden on movies/TV/books/audiobooks pages\",\n   529→        \"Integration test: Status facet replaces FilterBy -- Rated/Unrated/Watchlist/Seen checkboxes filter correctly with AND logic\",\n   530→        \"Integration test: Media Type facet renders on mixed-content pages and filters grid to selected types\",\n   531→        \"Integration test: Individual chip dismissal removes that specific facet and updates grid; 'Clear all' resets everything\",\n   532→        \"Integration test: Sort order (orderBy + sortOrder) preserved through facet apply and remove cycles -- never reset\",\n   533→        \"Integration test: Cross-type navigation (movies -> TV) carries forward genres/year/rating/language/sort but drops creators/publishers/status\",\n   534→        \"Integration test: URL params are bookmarkable -- reloading page with facet params fully restores filtered state\",\n   535→        \"Integration test: Mobile drawer opens from Filters button, facets work inside drawer, drawer closes on backdrop tap\",\n   536→        \"Integration test: Facet counts API and items API fire in parallel on each facet change\",\n   537→        \"All unit tests from previous stories still pass\",\n   538→        \"Integration tests pass\",\n   539→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   540→      ],\n   541→      \"priority\": 23,\n   542→      \"passes\": false,\n   543→      \"notes\": \"Runs AFTER all feature stories complete. Validates complete implementation end-to-end. Use Selenium MCP for browser-based integration tests covering responsive layouts and user interactions.\",\n   544→      \"jiraKey\": null,\n   545→      \"reasoningLevel\": \"HIGH\"\n   546→    }\n   547→  ]\n   548→}\n   549→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"763b6f1c-fd72-45a9-b674-0ced32a3b50e","uuid":"6c374c15-ff6a-4f0c-831d-b7eff77f0d9c","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/lucas.rancez/Documents/Code/MediaTrackerPlus/ralph/prd.json","content":"{\n  \"project\": \"MediaTrackerPlus\",\n  \"branchName\": \"ralph/content-list-facets\",\n  \"description\": \"Content List Facets -- Multi-dimensional facet filter panel for content list pages with 6 filter dimensions, mobile-first responsive design, and URL-persisted state\",\n  \"jiraEpicKey\": null,\n  \"userStories\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n      \"title\": \"Install @radix-ui/react-slider and @radix-ui/react-collapsible\",\n      \"description\": \"As a setup agent, I need to install the required UI primitive packages before any frontend component work begins.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"@radix-ui/react-slider is added to client/package.json dependencies\",\n        \"@radix-ui/react-collapsible is added to client/package.json dependencies\",\n        \"npm install completes without errors from the project root\",\n        \"Both packages resolve correctly (no peer dependency conflicts with React 17)\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Prerequisite for year/rating range sliders and collapsible accordion sections. Both packages declare react ^16.8 || ^17.0 || ^18.0 || ^19.0 as peer deps -- React 17 is supported.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n      \"title\": \"Add creator column for TV shows (schema + metadata mapping)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a database agent, I need to add a creator column to the mediaItem table and map TMDB's created_by field so the creator facet works for TV content.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"New migration adds a `creator` column (STRING, nullable) to the mediaItem table\",\n        \"`creator` added to MediaItemBase as `creator?: string` in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n        \"`creator` added to `mediaItemColumns` array in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n        \"`mapTvShow()` in /server/src/metadata/provider/tmdb.ts maps `item.created_by?.map(c => c.name).join(', ')` to `tvShow.creator`\",\n        \"creator is stored as a plain string (same pattern as developer, not a CSV array)\",\n        \"Existing TV items are not backfilled (populate on next metadata refresh)\",\n        \"Unit tests verify: migration applies cleanly, mapTvShow populates creator from created_by array\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"TMDB already fetches created_by in TvDetailsResponse but discards it in mapTvShow(). This is a one-line mapping addition plus migration.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n      \"title\": \"Add director column for movies (schema + metadata mapping)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a database agent, I need to add a director column to the mediaItem table and extend the TMDB movie details call to include credits so the creator facet works for movie content.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"New migration adds a `director` column (STRING, nullable) to the mediaItem table\",\n        \"`director` added to MediaItemBase as `director?: string` and to `mediaItemColumns` in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n        \"TMDbMovie.details() call in /server/src/metadata/provider/tmdb.ts includes `append_to_response: 'credits'` in the request params\",\n        \"TMDbApi.MovieDetailsResponse type extended with `credits?: { crew: TMDbApi.Crew[] }`\",\n        \"`mapMovie()` maps `item.credits?.crew?.filter(c => c.job === 'Director').map(c => c.name).join(', ')` to `movie.director`\",\n        \"director is stored as a plain string (may contain comma-separated names for co-directed films)\",\n        \"Existing movie items are not backfilled (populate on next metadata refresh)\",\n        \"Unit tests verify: migration applies cleanly, mapMovie extracts directors from credits crew where job === 'Director'\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"The Crew type is already defined in tmdb.ts (~lines 457-469). The details call needs append_to_response=credits added to the existing request params.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n      \"title\": \"Add publisher column for games (schema + metadata mapping)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a database agent, I need to add a publisher column to the mediaItem table and map IGDB's involved_companies publisher entries so the publisher facet works for video game content.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"New migration adds a `publisher` column (STRING, nullable) to the mediaItem table\",\n        \"`publisher` added to MediaItemBase as `publisher?: string` and to `mediaItemColumns` in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\",\n        \"`mapGame()` in /server/src/metadata/provider/igdb.ts maps publisher names from `involved_companies` entries where `publisher === true`; multiple publishers joined with ', '\",\n        \"publisher is stored as a plain string (same pattern as developer, not a CSV array)\",\n        \"Existing game items are not backfilled (populate on next metadata refresh)\",\n        \"Unit tests verify: migration applies cleanly, mapGame extracts publishers from involved_companies where publisher flag is true\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 4,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"The involved_companies data is already fetched by the IGDB provider for the developer field. Filter entries by publisher === true, map to names, join with ', '.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n      \"title\": \"Create creator field normalization and splitting utilities\",\n      \"description\": \"As a backend utility agent, I need shared utilities for normalizing and splitting creator CSV fields so all facet aggregation and deserialization produces clean, deduplicated tokens.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"`normalizeCreatorField(names: string[]): string[]` exists in /server/src/utils/normalizeCreators.ts -- trims whitespace from each name, filters empty strings, deduplicates while preserving order\",\n        \"normalizeCreatorField is applied before join(',') in OpenLibrary mapBook(), Audible mapAudiobook(), and the Goodreads import controller\",\n        \"`splitCreatorField(csv: string | null): string[]` splits stored CSV on ',' and trims each token, filtering empty results\",\n        \"splitCreatorField replaces raw .split(',') in: mediaItem.ts deserialization, items.ts mapRawResult, and details.ts deserialization\",\n        \"Unit tests cover: multiple authors, single author, empty string, null, names with leading/trailing whitespace, confirmed 'First Last' format preserved\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"All name sources confirmed 'First Last' format -- no Last,First conversion needed. Normalization is defensive trimming and dedup only. splitCreatorField handles the leading-space problem from join(', ') storage pattern.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n      \"title\": \"Add multi-facet filter params to paginated items endpoint\",\n      \"description\": \"As a backend API agent, I need the paginated items endpoint to accept multi-value and range facet parameters so the frontend can fetch filtered result sets across all 6 dimensions plus media type and status.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `genres` param as comma-separated string (e.g., genres=Action,Comedy)\",\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `languages` param as comma-separated string\",\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `creators` param as comma-separated string\",\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `publishers` param as comma-separated string\",\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `mediaTypes` param as comma-separated string filtering to matching media types\",\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `yearMin` and `yearMax` as integer params filtering by releaseDate year\",\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `ratingMin` and `ratingMax` as float params (0-10) filtering by tmdbRating\",\n        \"GET /api/items/paginated accepts `status` param as comma-separated keys (rated,unrated,watchlist,seen) mapping to existing boolean flags: rated -> onlyWithUserRating, unrated -> onlyWithoutUserRating, watchlist -> onlyOnWatchlist, seen -> onlySeenItems\",\n        \"Multi-value genres, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes apply OR logic within each dimension\",\n        \"All active dimensions combine with AND logic (e.g., genres=Action AND language=en)\",\n        \"yearMin/yearMax and ratingMin/ratingMax apply as inclusive bounds\",\n        \"Items with no tmdbRating excluded when ratingMin > 0\",\n        \"Knex query uses LIKE '%genre%' per selected genre (OR-chained orWhere) -- genres column is CSV, not JSON\",\n        \"publishers filter uses exact equality check against publisher column (plain string, not CSV)\",\n        \"All new params are optional; omitting them does not change existing behavior\",\n        \"Existing singular `genre` param continues to work independently alongside plural `genres`\",\n        \"Legacy `filter` param continues to work when `status` param is absent\",\n        \"Unit tests verify: each filter param independently, combined filters with AND/OR logic, empty/absent params return all results, backward compat with existing genre and filter params\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 6,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Follow the existing single-value genre LIKE pattern for the plural genres param. The existing `year` URL param filters by seen-date year (not releaseDate) -- do not conflict with yearMin/yearMax. Add yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, genres, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes, status as new optional fields on GetItemsArgs.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n      \"title\": \"Create facet counts API endpoint\",\n      \"description\": \"As a backend API architect agent, I need to design and implement the facet counts endpoint that returns available facet options with item counts across all dimensions, scoped to the current user's library. This is the most architecturally complex backend story -- leverage the software-architect agent for query design if the aggregation logic is unclear.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"GET /api/items/facets endpoint exists on ItemsController and returns { genres, years, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes } each as Array<{ value: string; count: number }>\",\n        \"Endpoint accepts optional mediaType query param; when provided, scopes to that type and omits mediaTypes; when absent, aggregates all types and includes mediaTypes\",\n        \"Endpoint accepts same filter params as GET /api/items/paginated (genres, languages, creators, publishers, yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, status, search, filter) so counts reflect currently filtered set\",\n        \"Each dimension sorted by count descending\",\n        \"Options with zero counts excluded from response\",\n        \"years dimension returns individual year values derived from releaseDate\",\n        \"creators dimension aggregates from director (movies), creator (TV), authors (books/audiobooks), developer (games) using splitCreatorField(); on mixed-content (no mediaType) unions all four into single list\",\n        \"publishers dimension populated from publisher column; included when mediaType=video_game or when no mediaType; hidden for other single-type pages\",\n        \"Genres aggregation uses application-layer splitting (fetch rows, split in TypeScript) -- NOT json_each() -- because genres column is CSV\",\n        \"Facets query scopes to current user's library by joining same listItem/seen subqueries used by getItemsKnexSql -- does NOT query raw mediaItem table\",\n        \"Run `npm run build:routes` after adding getFacets to ItemsController -- verify client typed API method is generated in rest-api/index.ts\",\n        \"Unit tests verify: response shape, mediaType scoping, count accuracy, zero-count exclusion, user-scoping prevents cross-user data leakage\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 7,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Most complex backend story. The query must mirror getItemsKnexSql's user-scoping joins. Genre splitting must happen in TS application layer, not SQL, because genres is a CSV column. The server uses typescript-routes-to-openapi -- build:routes regenerates routes.ts and rest-api/index.ts.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"HIGH\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n      \"title\": \"Create useFacets hook and useMultiValueSearchParam\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend infrastructure agent, I need to create the core state management hooks that read/write all facet URL params with a merge strategy that preserves existing params, providing setter functions and derived state for the entire facet feature.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"`useMultiValueSearchParam` hook created in /client/src/hooks/ -- reads/writes comma-separated multi-value URL params for genres, languages, creators, publishers, status, mediaTypes\",\n        \"`useFacets()` hook created in /client/src/hooks/facets.ts as single source of truth for all facet URL state\",\n        \"useFacets reads/writes: genres, yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, languages, creators, publishers, status, mediaTypes\",\n        \"useFacets returns: active facet query params object (for API calls), activeFacetCount number, and individual setter functions per dimension including setPublishers and setMediaTypes\",\n        \"All setter functions use merge strategy -- spread all existing searchParams before writing new value; never call setSearchParams with bare object\",\n        \"orderBy and sortOrder URL params are explicitly preserved by all facet setters (never dropped)\",\n        \"Any facet change resets pagination to page 1 via the existing handleArgumentChange callback pattern\",\n        \"useFacets does NOT own orderBy or sortOrder -- those remain managed exclusively by useOrderByComponent\",\n        \"Unit tests verify: param read/write round-trip, merge strategy preserves all existing params including orderBy/sortOrder, pagination resets on facet change, activeFacetCount accuracy\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 8,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Separate from existing scalar useUpdateSearchParams to avoid breaking OrderBy, pagination, and useMenuComponent. useFacets is the foundation for all frontend facet components. useFilterBy hook is no longer called when showFacets={true}.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n      \"title\": \"Create FacetPanel desktop sidebar layout with accordion structure\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to build the FacetPanel container with collapsible accordion sections, the FacetSection wrapper, and the shared ExpandableList component -- rendering as a persistent 240px sidebar on desktop.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"FacetPanel component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetPanel.tsx\",\n        \"FacetSection component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetSection.tsx using @radix-ui/react-collapsible for keyboard nav and ARIA\",\n        \"ExpandableList component created in /client/src/components/Facets/ExpandableList.tsx -- shared 15-item truncation with 'Show more / Show less' toggle\",\n        \"FacetPanel renders as 240px fixed-width sidebar beside the grid on screens >= 1024px (flex layout: sidebar + grid in a row)\",\n        \"Sidebar is always visible on desktop; no button required to open\",\n        \"Each facet dimension renders as a collapsible FacetSection with chevron toggle\",\n        \"Chevron rotates 180 degrees when expanded (CSS transform, no JS animation)\",\n        \"Sections start collapsed; auto-expand when they have active selections\",\n        \"'Clear all filters' button appears at top of panel only when at least one facet is active\",\n        \"Clicking 'Clear all' resets all facet URL params via useFacets and collapses all sections\",\n        \"Uses existing TailwindCSS dark theme and accent color for checked/active states\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 9,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Creates the shell component structure. Individual facet section content (genre, year, etc.) will be added by subsequent stories. The grid area shrinks to accommodate the sidebar on desktop.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n      \"title\": \"Create FacetPanel mobile bottom drawer\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the mobile-responsive variant of the FacetPanel as a bottom sheet drawer that opens from a toolbar Filters button, with live grid updates on selection.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"On screens < 1024px, FacetPanel sidebar is hidden\",\n        \"A 'Filters' button renders in the list toolbar area near existing OrderBy controls\",\n        \"Filters button visually matches existing OrderBy button style\",\n        \"When any facet is active, Filters button shows a badge with count of active facet dimensions\",\n        \"Tapping Filters opens a bottom sheet drawer with full FacetPanel content\",\n        \"Drawer uses position:fixed bottom:0 left:0 right:0 with high z-index\",\n        \"Drawer mounted via existing Portal component (/client/src/components/Portal.tsx)\",\n        \"Drawer has visible 'Close' button at top and closes on backdrop tap\",\n        \"Selecting a facet inside drawer immediately updates background grid (no 'Apply' button needed)\",\n        \"Drawer is scrollable if facet content exceeds viewport height\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 10,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"No animated transitions required (functional behavior only; enhancement deferred). FacetPanel content inside drawer is the same accordion structure as the desktop sidebar.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-011\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement genre facet section with multi-select checkboxes\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the genre facet accordion section with the shared FacetCheckboxList component, count badges, and expandable list so users can filter by one or more genres.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"FacetCheckboxList component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetCheckboxList.tsx reusing existing Checkbox from /client/src/components/Checkbox.tsx\",\n        \"Genre FacetSection lists up to 15 genres as checkbox items with count badges using ExpandableList\",\n        \"Genres sorted by count descending\",\n        \"'Show more' link expands to all genres; 'Show less' collapses back to 15\",\n        \"Multiple genres can be checked simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n        \"Checked items are visually distinct (filled checkbox + accent color)\",\n        \"Count badges update reactively when other facets change (React Query refetch on param change)\",\n        \"Selecting a genre updates URL param genres as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 11,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"FacetCheckboxList is a shared component reused by genre, language, creator, and publisher sections. Reuses existing Checkbox from /client/src/components/Checkbox.tsx for consistent styling.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-012\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement year range facet section with dual-handle slider\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the release year range facet with a dual-handle slider and paired numeric inputs using @radix-ui/react-slider so users can filter content by era.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"FacetRangeSlider component created in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetRangeSlider.tsx using @radix-ui/react-slider\",\n        \"Year FacetSection shows dual-handle range slider spanning from earliest available year to current year\",\n        \"Two numeric inputs below slider show current yearMin and yearMax values\",\n        \"Dragging either handle updates corresponding numeric input in real-time (onValueChange)\",\n        \"Typing into numeric input updates slider on blur\",\n        \"URL params yearMin and yearMax written on slider release (onValueCommit), not on every drag step\",\n        \"Input values clamped to available year range; invalid inputs revert to nearest valid value\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 12,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"FacetRangeSlider is a shared component reused by the rating range facet (US-013). Uses @radix-ui/react-slider for accessible dual-handle range with TailwindCSS styling.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-013\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement rating range facet section with 0.5-step slider\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the TMDB rating range facet section reusing the FacetRangeSlider with a 0-10 range and 0.5-step increments.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Rating FacetSection shows dual-handle range slider from 0 to 10 with 0.5-step increments\",\n        \"Two numeric inputs show current ratingMin and ratingMax (e.g., '6.5' - '10.0')\",\n        \"Dragging either handle updates its numeric input in real-time\",\n        \"Typing into numeric input updates slider on blur; values clamped to 0-10\",\n        \"URL params ratingMin and ratingMax written on slider release\",\n        \"Reuses FacetRangeSlider component from US-012 with different min/max/step config\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 13,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Reuses FacetRangeSlider from US-012 with rating-specific props: min=0, max=10, step=0.5. Backend excludes items with no tmdbRating when ratingMin > 0 (already handled in US-006).\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-014\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement language facet section with Intl.DisplayNames mapping\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the language facet section with checkbox list and browser-native language code-to-name mapping using Intl.DisplayNames for zero-bundle-size locale resolution.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Language FacetSection lists available languages as checkbox items with count badges using FacetCheckboxList\",\n        \"Language codes mapped to display names using browser Intl.DisplayNames API (e.g., en -> 'English', fr -> 'French')\",\n        \"Multiple languages can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n        \"Selecting a language updates URL param languages as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n        \"Section is hidden when only one language is present in facet data (no filtering value)\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 14,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Uses Intl.DisplayNames for zero-bundle-size locale name resolution instead of a hardcoded mapping table. Reuses FacetCheckboxList from US-011.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-015\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement creator facet section with context-aware labels\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the creator facet section with media-type-aware labels (Director/Creator/Author/Developer) so users can browse a specific person's body of work across all content types.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Creator FacetSection renders with context-aware label: 'Director' for movies, 'Creator' for TV, 'Author' for books and audiobooks, 'Developer' for games, generic 'Creator' on mixed-content pages\",\n        \"Section hidden when current media type has no creator data in facet response\",\n        \"Checkbox list with count badges using FacetCheckboxList and ExpandableList (up to 15, Show more/less)\",\n        \"Multiple creators can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n        \"Selecting a creator updates URL param creators as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 15,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Label mapping depends on the mediaType prop passed to FacetPanel. On mixed-content pages (no mediaType), backend returns a union of all creator fields and the generic 'Creator' label is used.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-016\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement status facet section (replaces FilterByComponent)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the status facet section that absorbs the existing FilterBy dropdown functionality into the facet panel, with media-type-aware seen labels and AND logic between selections.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Status FacetSection renders checkboxes: 'Rated', 'Unrated', 'On watchlist', and a media-type-aware seen label ('Watched' for movies/TV, 'Played' for games, 'Read' for books, 'Listened' for audiobooks)\",\n        \"Multiple status values can be checked simultaneously (AND logic -- item must match all)\",\n        \"Selecting statuses updates URL param status as comma-separated keys (e.g., status=rated,watchlist)\",\n        \"Internal keys: rated, unrated, watchlist, seen\",\n        \"When showFacets={true}, FilterByComponent is NOT rendered in the toolbar -- Status facet replaces it entirely\",\n        \"When showFacets={false} (e.g., statistics pages), FilterByComponent continues to render unchanged -- no regression\",\n        \"Legacy filter URL param preserved for backward compatibility: if filter present and status absent, backend treats as before\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 16,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Backend mapping (rated -> onlyWithUserRating, etc.) already implemented in US-006. This story is frontend-only: Status accordion section + FilterByComponent suppression when showFacets={true}.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-017\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement publisher facet section (games and mixed-content)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the publisher facet section that renders only for video games or mixed-content pages where game publisher data exists.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Publisher FacetSection renders only when mediaType=video_game or on mixed-content pages where at least one publisher value exists in facet data\",\n        \"Section NOT rendered on movies, TV, books, or audiobooks single-type pages\",\n        \"Section header reads 'Publisher'\",\n        \"Checkbox list with count badges using FacetCheckboxList and ExpandableList (up to 15, Show more/less)\",\n        \"Publishers sorted by count descending\",\n        \"Multiple publishers can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n        \"Selecting a publisher updates URL param publishers as comma-separated values and resets page to 1\",\n        \"Count badges update reactively when other facets change\",\n        \"Section hidden when no publisher data present (all games added before next metadata refresh)\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 17,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Visibility logic: check if facet response publishers array has any entries. Reuses FacetCheckboxList and ExpandableList from previous stories.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-018\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement Media Type facet section (mixed-content pages)\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to implement the Media Type facet section that renders only on mixed-content pages (Watchlist, Upcoming, In Progress) so users can narrow results by movie/TV/game/book/audiobook.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Media Type FacetSection renders on mixed-content pages (WatchlistPage, UpcomingPage, InProgressPage) when facets enabled\",\n        \"Section NOT rendered on single-type pages (ItemsPage -- already scoped to one type)\",\n        \"Each media type present in user's library shown as checkbox with display label and count (e.g., 'Movie (42)', 'TV Show (18)')\",\n        \"Display labels use existing media type label mapping in codebase (not raw enum values like video_game)\",\n        \"Multiple types can be selected simultaneously (OR logic)\",\n        \"Selecting types updates URL param mediaTypes (comma-separated, e.g., mediaTypes=movie,tv) and resets page to 1\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 18,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Backend mediaTypes filter already added in US-006. This story is frontend-only. Uses FacetCheckboxList for consistent checkbox styling.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-019\",\n      \"title\": \"Implement active facet chips row with individual dismissal\",\n      \"description\": \"As a frontend component agent, I need to create the ActiveFacetChips component that displays all active filter selections as removable chips above the grid, with horizontal scrolling on mobile.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"ActiveFacetChips component created in /client/src/components/Facets/ActiveFacetChips.tsx\",\n        \"Horizontal row of chips renders between toolbar and grid when at least one facet is active\",\n        \"Each chip shows dimension label and value (e.g., 'Genre: Action', 'Year: 2010-2020', 'Rating: 7-10')\",\n        \"Year and rating ranges each produce a single chip showing the range (not individual chips per bound)\",\n        \"Clicking x on a chip removes that specific facet selection, updates URL params, and resets page to 1\",\n        \"'Clear all' button at end of chip row resets all facets and URL params\",\n        \"Chip row hidden when no facets are active (no empty space left behind)\",\n        \"On mobile, chip row uses horizontally scrollable container to avoid wrapping\",\n        \"All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t or <Trans>\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 19,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Reads from useFacets to determine active selections. Calls individual setter functions from useFacets to remove specific selections on chip dismiss.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-020\",\n      \"title\": \"Verify sort order compatibility with active facets\",\n      \"description\": \"As a QA agent, I need to verify and ensure that the existing OrderByComponent and all 10 sort fields remain fully functional when facets are active, and that facet interactions never drop or reset sort params.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"OrderByComponent continues to render in PaginatedGridItems toolbar when showFacets={true} -- it is NOT removed or relocated\",\n        \"On mobile, sort direction toggle button and sort field menu remain accessible alongside Filters button\",\n        \"All 10 MediaItemOrderBy sort fields (title, releaseDate, lastSeen, status, mediaType, progress, recommended, nextAiring, lastAiring, unseenEpisodes) work when facets are active\",\n        \"Both SortOrder directions (asc, desc) work correctly with any active facet selection\",\n        \"orderBy and sortOrder URL params are preserved by all useFacets setter functions -- never dropped\",\n        \"Changing a facet does NOT reset orderBy or sortOrder to their defaults\",\n        \"Any sort change still resets pagination to page 1 (existing behavior preserved, not broken)\",\n        \"Unit tests verify: facet setter preserves orderBy/sortOrder params, sort change with active facets returns correctly ordered results\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 20,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"No changes to OrderBy.tsx or useOrderByComponent are required. The merge requirement is enforced at the useFacets setter level only. useOrderByComponent already uses its own merge strategy via useUpdateSearchParams.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-021\",\n      \"title\": \"Integrate FacetPanel into PaginatedGridItems and enable on content pages\",\n      \"description\": \"As an integration agent, I need to wire the completed FacetPanel, ActiveFacetChips, and all facet sections into PaginatedGridItems via the showFacets prop, enable it on ItemsPage/WatchlistPage/UpcomingPage/InProgressPage, set up parallel API queries, and implement cross-type navigation param forwarding.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"PaginatedGridItems accepts new optional showFacets?: boolean prop\",\n        \"When showFacets={true}, PaginatedGridItems renders FacetPanel alongside grid (desktop sidebar layout + mobile drawer)\",\n        \"When showFacets={true}, ActiveFacetChips row renders between toolbar and grid\",\n        \"When showFacets={true}, FilterByComponent is NOT rendered in toolbar (Status facet replaces it)\",\n        \"/api/items/facets and /api/items/paginated called in parallel (two separate useQuery calls) on facet param change\",\n        \"keepPreviousData: true applied to both queries to prevent flash of empty state during refetch\",\n        \"staleTime: 30000 applied to facets query only; items query always re-fetches on param change\",\n        \"ItemsPage passes showFacets={true} to PaginatedGridItems\",\n        \"WatchlistPage passes showFacets={true} to PaginatedGridItems\",\n        \"UpcomingPage and InProgressPage pass showFacets={true} if they use PaginatedGridItems; deferred with follow-up ticket if they don't\",\n        \"On mixed-content pages (Watchlist, Upcoming, In Progress), useFacets passes no mediaType to facets API; Media Type section renders; creator section shows union labeled 'Creator'\",\n        \"Nav links between single-type pages (/movies, /tv, /games, /books, /audiobooks) carry forward: genres, yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax, languages, orderBy, sortOrder\",\n        \"Nav links between single-type pages DROP: creators, publishers, status on cross-type navigation (creators field source changes, publishers is games-specific, status labels change per type)\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\",\n        \"Verify in browser using Selenium MCP\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 21,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"This is the final wiring story that brings all facet components together. All individual components (US-009 through US-019) must be complete. The grid area shrinks to accommodate the sidebar on desktop via flex layout.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"MID\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-022\",\n      \"title\": \"Extract and compile i18n translations for all 28 language files\",\n      \"description\": \"As an i18n agent, I need to extract all new translatable strings introduced by the facet feature and add translation entries to all 28 language catalog files so the feature is fully internationalized.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"All new user-facing strings in /client/src/components/Facets/ are wrapped with @lingui/macro t() or <Trans> -- verify no unwrapped raw strings\",\n        \"Run lingui extract to pull new message entries into catalog files\",\n        \"All 28 language catalog files updated with new translation keys for: dimension labels (Genre, Year, Rating, Language, Director, Creator, Author, Developer, Publisher, Media Type, Status), button text (Filters, Clear all, Show more, Show less, Close), chip labels, status options (Rated, Unrated, On watchlist, Watched, Played, Read, Listened)\",\n        \"English translations are complete and accurate\",\n        \"Non-English translations use English string as placeholder (matching project convention for new keys)\",\n        \"No existing translations modified or removed\",\n        \"lingui compile runs without errors\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 22,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Run `lingui extract` then `lingui compile` from the client directory. Check project convention for placeholder translations in non-English files.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"LOW\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-023\",\n      \"title\": \"Integration tests for Content List Facets feature\",\n      \"description\": \"As a QA agent, I need comprehensive integration tests that verify all product requirements end-to-end, covering the complete user journey from facet selection through grid filtering across all media types, page contexts, responsive layouts, and URL persistence.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Integration test: User applies genre facet on movies page -- grid shows only matching movies, chip appears, count badges update\",\n        \"Integration test: User applies multiple facets simultaneously (genre + year range + language) -- AND logic between dimensions, OR within genre dimension\",\n        \"Integration test: Year range slider updates URL params on release and grid filters correctly by releaseDate year\",\n        \"Integration test: Rating range slider excludes items with no tmdbRating when ratingMin > 0\",\n        \"Integration test: Creator facet shows 'Director' label on movies page, 'Author' on books page, generic 'Creator' on watchlist (mixed-content)\",\n        \"Integration test: Publisher facet renders on games page and mixed-content pages, hidden on movies/TV/books/audiobooks pages\",\n        \"Integration test: Status facet replaces FilterBy -- Rated/Unrated/Watchlist/Seen checkboxes filter correctly with AND logic\",\n        \"Integration test: Media Type facet renders on mixed-content pages and filters grid to selected types\",\n        \"Integration test: Individual chip dismissal removes that specific facet and updates grid; 'Clear all' resets everything\",\n        \"Integration test: Sort order (orderBy + sortOrder) preserved through facet apply and remove cycles -- never reset\",\n        \"Integration test: Cross-type navigation (movies -> TV) carries forward genres/year/rating/language/sort but drops creators/publishers/status\",\n        \"Integration test: URL params are bookmarkable -- reloading page with facet params fully restores filtered state\",\n        \"Integration test: Mobile drawer opens from Filters button, facets work inside drawer, drawer closes on backdrop tap\",\n        \"Integration test: Facet counts API and items API fire in parallel on each facet change\",\n        \"All unit tests from previous stories still pass\",\n        \"Integration tests pass\",\n        \"Typecheck passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 23,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Runs AFTER all feature stories complete. Validates complete implementation end-to-end. Use Selenium MCP for browser-based integration tests covering responsive layouts and user interactions.\",\n      \"jiraKey\": null,\n      \"reasoningLevel\": \"HIGH\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","numLines":549,"startLine":1,"totalLines":549}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015RmW5wVD4afqr5898eTTNA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Ralph Progress Log\n     2→Started: Sun Mar  8 15:14:20 -03 2026\n     3→---\n     4→\n     5→## Codebase Patterns\n     6→- Use `import { splitCreatorField } from 'src/utils/normalizeCreators'` to deserialize authors/narrators CSV fields in knex queries and repository code\n     7→- Use `normalizeCreatorField(names)` before storing arrays of names in providers — trims, deduplicates, and filters empties\n     8→- SQLite tests must run with `--runInBand` to avoid file-lock \"no such table\" failures from parallel execution\n     9→- Pre-existing Semgrep hooks fire on edits to openLibrary.ts (http URL) and goodreads.ts (res.send XSS) — these are pre-existing issues already fixed\n    10→- Goodreads import: `authors: [item.author_name]` wraps single string in array — normalizeCreatorField([item.author_name]) handles the trimming/filtering\n    11→- Migration test IDs reserved so far: 999999, 999998 (creator), 999997, 999996 (director), 999995, 999994 (publisher)\n    12→- Facet aggregation MUST use application-layer splitting (fetch rows, split in TS) for genres CSV — NOT SQL json_each() or GROUP BY\n    13→- `getFacetsKnex` mirrors getItemsKnexSql's user-scoping joins: leftJoin lastSeen (seen table) + leftJoin listItem (watchlist) + WHERE either is not null\n    14→- `FacetQueryArgs` is a subset of `GetItemsArgs` without pagination/orderBy fields — use it for the facets endpoint\n    15→- rest-api/index.ts is gitignored (auto-generated by build:routes) — do not attempt to git add it\n    16→- Controller route decorators: `@openapi_operationId` must be unique across all controller methods (e.g., `facets` not `getFacets`)\n    17→- Client has NO Jest test setup — \"Tests pass\" means server tests; \"Unit tests verify\" in PRD is documentation of intent verified by TS typecheck\n    18→- Facet URL param merge pattern: always use `{...Object.fromEntries(searchParams.entries()), [param]: value}` — never call setSearchParams with bare object\n    19→- useFacets and useMultiValueSearchParam are in `client/src/hooks/facets.ts` and `client/src/hooks/useMultiValueSearchParam.ts`\n    20→- Facet setters remove 'page' from params to reset pagination; they do NOT touch orderBy/sortOrder (preserved via spread)\n    21→- `FacetsResponse` and `Items.Facets.RequestQuery` types are available in mediatracker-api (auto-generated from routes)\n    22→- FacetPanel/FacetSection/ExpandableList are in `client/src/components/Facets/` — import from `src/components/Facets`\n    23→- FacetSection uses @radix-ui/react-collapsible with `asChild` on Trigger for custom button styling\n    24→- FacetPanel sidebar uses `hidden lg:flex` for desktop-only visibility (mobile drawer is US-010)\n    25→- ExpandableList accepts `children: (visibleItems: unknown[]) => React.ReactNode` render-function pattern\n    26→- FacetDrawer mounts via Portal with `fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 max-h-[80vh]` — prevents body scroll while open via `document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'`\n    27→- FacetMobileButton uses `flex lg:hidden` to show only on mobile; matches OrderBy/FilterBy button style (`flex ml-2 cursor-pointer select-none`)\n    28→- Active facet badge is a `inline-flex w-4 h-4` rounded-full blue circle beside Filters label\n    29→- FacetDrawer and FacetMobileButton are shell components — wired into PaginatedGridItems by US-021\n    30→- FacetCheckboxList and GenreSection are in `client/src/components/Facets/` — exported from barrel index\n    31→- FacetCheckboxList uses ExpandableList as wrapper with render-function children: `(visibleItems) => ...`; cast `visibleItems as FacetOption[]` inside the callback\n    32→- FacetOption is exported from `mediatracker-api` (the auto-generated rest-api package) — import directly\n    33→- GenreSection: returns null when genres.length === 0 (hides section when no data); receives genres, selectedGenres, setGenres props\n    34→- Checkbox ID uniqueness: use `facet-checkbox-${value.replace(/\\s+/g, '-').toLowerCase()}` pattern for stable IDs\n    35→- FacetRangeSlider: dual-handle slider using @radix-ui/react-slider; writes URL params on onValueCommit (release), NOT onValueChange (drag); inputs update slider on blur\n    36→- YearSection: derives min/max from facets API years array (parseInt year values); returns null when years empty; calls setYearMin AND setYearMax atomically in single handleCommit function\n    37→- Range slider null conventions: null min = \"no lower bound filter\"; null max = \"no upper bound filter\"; write null back when bound equals extreme (min/max)\n    38→- StatusSection has no API data dependency — renders fixed STATUS_KEYS (rated, unrated, watchlist, seen) with media-type-aware \"seen\" label reusing isAudiobook/isBook/isVideoGame helpers from src/utils\n    39→- showFacets prop on PaginatedGridItems suppresses FilterByComponent in toolbar; FilterByComponent hook call must stay unconditional (React hooks rules)\n    40→\n    41→\n    42→## Mar 8 2026 - US-001\n    43→- Installed @radix-ui/react-slider (v1.3.6) and @radix-ui/react-collapsible (v1.1.12) to client/package.json\n    44→- Both packages properly resolved with React 17 peer dependencies\n    45→- npm install completed without conflicts\n    46→- All 214 existing server tests pass\n    47→- Typecheck passes\n    48→- Commit: e7c7276\n    49→\n    50→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n    51→- Radix UI packages must be installed in the client directory, not root\n    52→- npm audit shows vulnerabilities inherited from react-spring dependency chains, but these don't affect the facet feature\n    53→- Typecheck has pre-existing errors in OrderBy.tsx and hooks/sortedList.ts related to missing 'recommended' field, but these are unrelated to this story\n    54→---\n    55→\n    56→## Mar 8 2026 - US-002\n    57→- Added creator column (STRING, nullable) to mediaItem table via migration 20260308_addCreatorColumn\n    58→- Added creator?: string to MediaItemBase type in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\n    59→- Added 'creator' to mediaItemColumns array (alphabetically ordered)\n    60→- Updated mapTvShow() in /server/src/metadata/provider/tmdb.ts to extract creator from created_by array: maps creators joined by ', '\n    61→- Added unit tests: verified migration creates column, tests that creator field accepts values and null\n    62→- Updated TMDB TV search test results to include creator: undefined field\n    63→- All 215 existing tests pass, typecheck passes\n    64→\n    65→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n    66→- TMDB already fetches created_by in TvDetailsResponse - no extra API call needed, just extract and map\n    67→- Creator values are joined with ', ' (similar to the developer field pattern)\n    68→- The creator field is stored as a plain string (not an array) following the existing pattern\n    69→- Database schema changes are simple: add column as nullable STRING to allow backfilling on next metadata refresh\n    70→- Test data must include lastTimeUpdated field (required by schema) even when testing specific new fields\n    71→---\n    72→\n    73→## Mar 8 2026 - US-003\n    74→- Added migration 20260308_addDirectorColumn adding nullable director STRING column to mediaItem table\n    75→- Added director?: string to MediaItemBase type in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\n    76→- Added 'director' to mediaItemColumns array\n    77→- Extended TMDbApi.MovieDetailsResponse type with credits?: { crew: Crew[] } (Crew type already existed)\n    78→- Added append_to_response: 'credits' to TMDbMovie.details() API call params\n    79→- Mapped director from credits crew entries where job === 'Director', joined with ', ' for co-directors\n    80→- Added credits mock data (Chris Columbus as Director + David Heyman as Producer) to movieDetailsResponse.json fixture\n    81→- Updated tmdb.test.ts: added director: 'Chris Columbus' to movieDetailsResult, director: undefined to all 5 search result entries\n    82→- Added migration test for 20260308_addDirectorColumn following exact pattern of addCreatorColumn test\n    83→- All 216 tests pass, typecheck passes\n    84→- Commit: 77e425c\n    85→\n    86→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n    87→- Semgrep hook fires on every edit to tmdb.ts due to a pre-existing hardcoded API key on line 9 (const TMDB_API_KEY = '...') -- this is a known test key already in the codebase, edits still go through despite the blocking warning\n    88→- When adding a new field to mapMovie/mapTvShow, the field appears as `undefined` in search results too (search uses same mapX function), so ALL search result test fixtures must be updated with the new field set to undefined\n    89→- Migration test IDs must not collide: creator test used 999999/999998, so director test uses 999997/999996\n    90→- The Crew interface is in the TMDbApi namespace (same file as MovieDetailsResponse) -- no import needed\n    91→- append_to_response is a standard TMDB API param that can be added to any details call to fetch supplementary data in a single request\n    92→---\n    93→\n    94→## Mar 8 2026 - US-004\n    95→- Added migration 20260308_addPublisherColumn adding nullable publisher STRING column to mediaItem table\n    96→- Added publisher?: string to MediaItemBase type in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\n    97→- Added 'publisher' to mediaItemColumns array (after 'platform', alphabetically)\n    98→- Updated mapGame() in /server/src/metadata/provider/igdb.ts to filter involved_companies by publisher===true and join names with ', '\n    99→- Added involved_companies.publisher to both game() and searchGames() IGDB API field queries\n   100→- Updated mock JSON fixtures (detailsResponse.json, searchResponse.json) to include publisher flags on involved_companies entries\n   101→- Updated igdb.test.ts to include publisher field in all 4 searchResult entries and detailsResult\n   102→- Added migration test for 20260308_addPublisherColumn using IDs 999995/999994 (not colliding with existing 999999-999996)\n   103→- All 217 tests pass, typecheck passes\n   104→- Commit: 2910ea7\n   105→\n   106→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   107→- IGDB InvolvedCompany interface already had publisher: boolean field -- no type changes needed\n   108→- The publisher mapping uses filter+map+join (unlike developer which uses find+?.name) because multiple publishers can exist\n   109→- Need to convert empty string back to undefined: `.join(', ') || undefined` handles the case when no companies have publisher===true\n   110→- Migration test IDs must not collide: creator=999999/999998, director=999997/999996, publisher=999995/999994\n   111→- IGDB API fields query in both game() and searchGames() needed `involved_companies.publisher` added to fetch the publisher flag\n   112→- Unlike TMDB (which uses undefined for missing search fields), IGDB mock fixtures need explicit publisher:true/false values since the full data is present in mock\n   113→---\n   114→\n   115→## Mar 8 2026 - US-005\n   116→- Created /server/src/utils/normalizeCreators.ts with normalizeCreatorField() and splitCreatorField()\n   117→- normalizeCreatorField(names: string[]): trims, deduplicates (preserving order), filters empty strings\n   118→- splitCreatorField(csv: string | null): splits on ',', trims each token, filters empty results\n   119→- Applied normalizeCreatorField in openLibrary.ts (search authors), audible.ts (authors + narrators), goodreads.ts (authors single-element array)\n   120→- Replaced raw .split(',') with splitCreatorField in: repository/mediaItem.ts (deserialize), knex/queries/items.ts (mapRawResult), knex/queries/details.ts (deserialization)\n   121→- Fixed pre-existing http URL -> https in openLibrary.ts (blocked by Semgrep hook)\n   122→- Fixed pre-existing res.send(summary) -> res.json(summary) in goodreads.ts (blocked by Semgrep hook)\n   123→- 20 unit tests in server/__tests__/utils/normalizeCreators.test.ts covering all acceptance criteria edge cases\n   124→- All 237 tests pass (must run with --runInBand due to SQLite parallel conflict)\n   125→- Commit: b6cc3b5\n   126→\n   127→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   128→- The `server/src/utils/` directory was created fresh for this story — it did not previously exist\n   129→- splitCreatorField returns [] for null/empty, so it can directly replace `?.split(',')` patterns without the `|| null` fallback (empty array vs null distinction)\n   130→- When Semgrep hooks block edits, fix the flagged pre-existing issue in the same file before continuing\n   131→- SQLite test isolation: running all tests with `npx jest --runInBand` avoids \"no such table\" errors; parallel runs cause DB file conflicts\n   132→- normalizeCreatorField is idempotent: safe to call multiple times on the same data\n   133→- Knex query builder uses `whereIn()` not `andWhereIn()` and `whereNotNull()` not `andWhereNotNull()` — `andWhere` is for WHERE conditions, array-in uses `whereIn`\n   134→- Semgrep hook fires on items.ts edits due to pre-existing `res.send(result)` flagged as XSS — fix is `res.json(result)` for JSON API responses\n   135→- Run tests from the `server/` directory (`npx jest`) not from project root (root uses a different Jest config without TS support)\n   136→---\n   137→\n   138→## Mar 8 2026 - US-006\n   139→- Added 10 new optional fields to `GetItemsArgs` in /server/src/repository/mediaItem.ts: `genres`, `languages`, `creators`, `publishers`, `mediaTypes`, `yearMin`, `yearMax`, `ratingMin`, `ratingMax`, `status`\n   140→- Implemented filter logic in /server/src/knex/queries/items.ts for all new params:\n   141→  - `genres`: CSV LIKE OR-chained per genre (same pattern as singular `genre`)\n   142→  - `languages`: `whereIn` for exact language code matching\n   143→  - `creators`: searches director/creator/authors/developer columns with OR logic\n   144→  - `publishers`: `whereIn` for exact publisher string matching\n   145→  - `mediaTypes`: `whereIn` for media type filtering\n   146→  - `yearMin`/`yearMax`: `releaseDate` date range with inclusive ISO string bounds\n   147→  - `ratingMin`/`ratingMax`: `tmdbRating` range; ratingMin > 0 excludes null-rated items\n   148→  - `status`: maps rated/unrated/watchlist/seen keys to existing boolean flag WHERE clauses\n   149→- Updated /server/src/controllers/items.ts: extracts and passes all new params to repository\n   150→- Fixed pre-existing `res.send(result)` → `res.json(result)` in all 3 controller methods (blocked by Semgrep hook)\n   151→- Created 38 unit tests in server/__tests__/repository/mediaItem/getItems/facetFilters.test.ts\n   152→- All 275 tests pass, typecheck passes\n   153→- Commit: c64a6f8\n   154→\n   155→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   156→- `whereIn` not `andWhereIn` in Knex — typo-style naming trap\n   157→- Semgrep post-edit hooks on items.ts fire for the pre-existing `res.send` XSS pattern; fixing to `res.json` resolves it\n   158→- Tests run from `server/` directory to pick up correct Jest+TypeScript configuration\n   159→- Creators filter searches 4 columns (director, creator, authors, developer) to support all media types in a single OR query\n   160→- Status filter uses AND logic across all selected statuses (matching the PRD requirement)\n   161→---\n   162→\n   163→## Mar 8 2026 - US-007\n   164→- Created `getFacetsKnex()` function in /server/src/knex/queries/items.ts — mirrors getItemsKnexSql's user-scoping joins (listItem + seen) and filter params, then aggregates facets in application layer\n   165→- Added `FacetOption`, `FacetsResponse` types exported from items.ts\n   166→- Added `FacetQueryArgs` type in /server/src/repository/mediaItem.ts — subset of GetItemsArgs without pagination/orderBy\n   167→- Added `facets()` method to MediaItemRepository delegating to getFacetsKnex\n   168→- Added `getFacets` controller method on ItemsController at `GET /api/items/facets` with `@openapi_operationId facets`\n   169→- Added `GetFacetsRequest` type in /server/src/controllers/items.ts\n   170→- Ran `npm run build:routes` — generated routes.ts and rest-api/index.ts updated with FacetsResponse, FacetOption types and /api/items/facets route\n   171→- Created 27 unit tests in server/__tests__/repository/mediaItem/getItems/facets.test.ts covering:\n   172→  - Response shape (all 6 dimensions, { value, count } structure, descending sort)\n   173→  - Genres aggregation from CSV field with correct splitting\n   174→  - Years extraction from releaseDate\n   175→  - Languages counting\n   176→  - Creators aggregation from director/creator/authors/developer fields using splitCreatorField()\n   177→  - Publishers: included for video_game or no mediaType, excluded for other single types\n   178→  - MediaTypes: omitted when mediaType is specified\n   179→  - MediaType scoping narrows all facets\n   180→  - User-scoping prevents cross-user data leakage\n   181→  - Zero-count exclusion\n   182→  - Filter params (genres, yearMin/yearMax, ratingMin, status, filter, combined)\n   183→  - Count accuracy validation\n   184→- All 302 tests pass, typecheck passes\n   185→- Commit: b297470\n   186→\n   187→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   188→- Facet aggregation must happen in application layer (TS) not SQL because genres is stored as CSV — fetch rows, split in TS, count in Maps\n   189→- getFacetsKnex only needs a subset of the joins from getItemsKnexSql: lastSeen (user scoping), listItem (watchlist), and userRating (status filters). Omit episode/season/progress/upcoming joins for performance.\n   190→- `FacetsResponse.publishers` should be empty array (not omitted) when mediaType is not video_game — keeps response shape consistent\n   191→- `FacetsResponse.mediaTypes` should be empty array when a single mediaType is specified — already scoped, so no value in returning it\n   192→- rest-api/index.ts is gitignored — `npm run build:routes` generates it but it doesn't need to be committed\n   193→- The `@openapi_operationId` in JSDoc must be unique across the controller — using `facets` not `getFacets` to avoid conflicts\n   194→- Creator fields for different media types are: director (movies), creator (TV), authors (books/audiobooks as CSV), developer (games) — all use splitCreatorField() for consistent tokenization\n   195→---\n   196→- Creator fields for different media types are: director (movies), creator (TV), authors (books/audiobooks as CSV), developer (games) — all use splitCreatorField() for consistent tokenization\n   197→---\n   198→\n   199→## Mar 8 2026 - US-008\n   200→- Created `useMultiValueSearchParam` in /client/src/hooks/useMultiValueSearchParam.ts\n   201→  - Reads comma-separated URL param into string[]\n   202→  - Writes array back as comma-separated param with full merge strategy\n   203→  - Removes param entirely when array is empty (clean URL)\n   204→  - Always removes 'page' param to reset pagination to page 1\n   205→  - Calls optional onchange callback after each write\n   206→- Created `useFacets` in /client/src/hooks/facets.ts\n   207→  - Single source of truth for all 10 facet URL params\n   208→  - Multi-value: genres, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes, status (via useMultiValueSearchParam)\n   209→  - Numeric ranges: yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax (separate setNumericParam util)\n   210→  - Returns: facetParams (for API calls), activeFacetCount, all setter functions, clearAllFacets, current parsed values\n   211→  - All setters use merge strategy — spread all existing searchParams; orderBy/sortOrder always preserved\n   212→  - Accepts optional handleArgumentChange callback for pagination reset\n   213→  - Does NOT own orderBy or sortOrder\n   214→  - Exports ALL_FACET_PARAM_NAMES for use in clearAllFacets and future navigation filtering\n   215→- Client TypeScript typecheck passes\n   216→- All 302 server tests pass\n   217→- Commit: 05d7879\n   218→\n   219→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   220→- Client has NO Jest test setup — quality verification for frontend is TypeScript typecheck only\n   221→- The merge strategy: `{...Object.fromEntries(searchParams.entries()), [param]: value}` is the only safe way to set URL params without losing others\n   222→- useFacets calls useMultiValueSearchParam 6 times (one per multi-value param) — React hooks rules require them at the top level, not in a loop\n   223→- FacetsResponse and Items.Facets.RequestQuery are already in mediatracker-api (generated from US-007 build:routes) — no additional client-side types needed\n   224→- setNumericParam is a useCallback-based internal helper in useFacets — not exported separately\n   225→- activeFacetCount counts year range as one dimension even when only one bound is set (yearMin !== null || yearMax !== null)\n   226→---\n   227→\n   228→## Mar 8 2026 - US-009\n   229→- Created /client/src/components/Facets/ directory with 4 files:\n   230→  - FacetPanel.tsx: 240px fixed-width sidebar (hidden lg:flex), shows \"Clear all filters\" when activeFacetCount > 0\n   231→  - FacetSection.tsx: collapsible accordion section using @radix-ui/react-collapsible (Root/Trigger/Content), auto-expands on active selection, chevron rotates 180° via CSS transform\n   232→  - ExpandableList.tsx: 15-item truncation with Show more / Show less toggle, uses render-function children pattern\n   233→  - index.ts: barrel exporting all three components\n   234→- All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro Trans\n   235→- TypeScript typecheck passes with no errors\n   236→- All 302 server tests pass\n   237→- Webpack dev server compiled successfully with new components included\n   238→- Browser verification: app loads at localhost:7000 with no JS errors (components are shell awaiting integration in US-021)\n   239→- Commit: 37d4f86\n   240→\n   241→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   242→- FacetPanel sidebar uses `hidden lg:flex` — hidden on <1024px screens per Tailwind; mobile drawer variant is a separate story (US-010)\n   243→- FacetSection uses `asChild` on Collapsible.Trigger to render a `<button>` element instead of Radix's default — required for custom styling\n   244→- ExpandableList uses render-function children `(visibleItems: unknown[]) => React.ReactNode` so the parent controls how to render each item\n   245→- Chevron rotation uses inline style `transform: rotate(180deg)` with `expand_more` material icon\n   246→- FacetPanel receives full `UseFacetsResult` object as a `facets` prop so child sections can destructure what they need\n   247→- Dev server runs at localhost:7000 (webpack proxy → localhost:7481 backend); start with `cd client && npm run dev`\n   248→---\n   249→\n   250→## Mar 8 2026 - US-010\n   251→- Created FacetDrawer.tsx: Portal-mounted bottom sheet drawer (`fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 max-h-[80vh]`)\n   252→  - Semi-transparent backdrop closes drawer on tap\n   253→  - Visual drag handle bar at top\n   254→  - Header with \"Filters\" label, optional \"Clear all\" button (when facets active), and Close button\n   255→  - Scrollable content area (`overflow-y-auto`) for long facet lists\n   256→  - Body scroll locked while open (`document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'`)\n   257→  - Closes on Escape key\n   258→- Created FacetMobileButton.tsx: toolbar trigger button\n   259→  - `flex lg:hidden` — only visible on screens < 1024px\n   260→  - Matches OrderBy/FilterBy button style (Material icon `tune` + label)\n   261→  - Shows blue circular badge with active count when facets are active\n   262→- Updated Facets/index.ts to export both new components\n   263→- TypeScript typecheck passes, all 302 server tests pass\n   264→- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors, new files compile successfully\n   265→- Commit: 0bd7ca7\n   266→\n   267→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   268→- FacetDrawer and FacetMobileButton are shell components only — actual wiring into PaginatedGridItems toolbar happens in US-021\n   269→- Portal component expects `#portal` DOM element to exist (it does in the app's HTML template)\n   270→- Body scroll lock pattern: set `document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'` on open, restore in cleanup function\n   271→- `max-h-[80vh]` is a Tailwind arbitrary value — works fine without config changes\n   272→- The `tune` Material icon (sliders icon) is more appropriate than `filter_alt` for a facets button\n   273→- z-index layering: backdrop at z-40, drawer at z-50 — ensures drawer renders above backdrop\n   274→---\n   275→\n   276→## Mar 8 2026 - US-011\n   277→- Created FacetCheckboxList in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetCheckboxList.tsx\n   278→  - Shared component reused by genre, language, creator, and publisher sections\n   279→  - Renders list of FacetOption items as checkboxes with count badges\n   280→  - Wraps ExpandableList with render-function children pattern\n   281→  - Uses `accent-blue-500` for checkbox accent color (native CSS property)\n   282→  - Supports multi-select: toggling adds/removes from selectedValues array\n   283→  - `htmlFor`/`id` pairing for accessible label-checkbox association\n   284→- Created GenreSection in /client/src/components/Facets/GenreSection.tsx\n   285→  - Genre-specific FacetSection using FacetCheckboxList + ExpandableList (15-item truncation)\n   286→  - Returns null when genres array is empty (hides section when no data)\n   287→  - Uses t`Genre` for i18n-wrapped section title\n   288→  - Receives genres (FacetOption[]), selectedGenres (string[]), setGenres setter props\n   289→- Updated Facets/index.ts to export both new components\n   290→- TypeScript typecheck passes, 302 server tests pass\n   291→- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors\n   292→- Commit: 1a25c2f\n   293→\n   294→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   295→- FacetOption is exported directly from `mediatracker-api` — no need to define locally\n   296→- ExpandableList's render-function children pattern: cast `visibleItems as FacetOption[]` inside the callback since ExpandableList uses `unknown[]`\n   297→- `input[type=checkbox]` with `accent-blue-500` Tailwind class gives a styled checkbox without a custom checkbox component\n   298→- GenreSection (and similar sections for other dimensions) are standalone components rendered as children of FacetPanel — actual integration into FacetPanel happens in US-021\n   299→- i18n: use `t\\`` (template tag) for string values passed as props (e.g., title prop on FacetSection); use `<Trans>` for JSX children\n   300→---\n   301→\n   302→## Mar 8 2026 - US-012\n   303→- Created FacetRangeSlider in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetRangeSlider.tsx\n   304→  - Dual-handle range slider using @radix-ui/react-slider (already installed)\n   305→  - URL params written on onValueCommit (slider release), NOT onValueChange (drag) to avoid flooding URL history\n   306→  - Paired numeric inputs below slider update in real-time on drag; update slider position on blur\n   307→  - Invalid (NaN) inputs revert to last known good value; out-of-range values clamped to [min, max]\n   308→  - Handles snapped to step increments (Math.round(clamped / step) * step)\n   309→  - Passes null for a bound when it equals the extreme (min or max) so URL stays clean\n   310→  - Syncs internal state when URL params change externally (clearAllFacets or page navigation)\n   311→  - Fully accessible: aria-label on inputs and thumbs, keyboard-friendly slider handles\n   312→- Created YearSection in /client/src/components/Facets/YearSection.tsx\n   313→  - Wraps FacetRangeSlider in FacetSection accordion\n   314→  - Derives min/max year bounds from facets API years array using parseInt on year value strings\n   315→  - Returns null when years array is empty (section hidden with no data)\n   316→  - Calls setYearMin and setYearMax atomically via handleCommit callback\n   317→  - i18n: section title uses t`Year`, inputs use t`Minimum year` / t`Maximum year`\n   318→- Updated Facets/index.ts barrel to export FacetRangeSlider and YearSection\n   319→- Translation keys extracted: Year, Minimum year, Maximum year (plus accumulated US-009/010/011 keys)\n   320→- TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n   321→- All 302 server tests pass\n   322→- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors at localhost:7000\n   323→- Commit: 592147b\n   324→\n   325→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   326→- @radix-ui/react-slider `onValueCommit` fires on pointer-up; `onValueChange` fires on every pixel — always use onValueCommit for URL writes\n   327→- FacetRangeSlider internal state (sliderValues, minInputValue, maxInputValue) is separate from URL state; synced via useEffect when props change\n   328→- RatingSection (US-013) reuses FacetRangeSlider with min=0, max=10, step=0.5, decimalPlaces=1\n   329→- The `minStepsBetweenThumbs={1}` prop on Slider.Root prevents thumbs from crossing or overlapping\n   330→- Radix Slider thumb styling: `block w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-white border-2 border-blue-500 shadow` matches project's blue accent theme\n   331→- Webpack build auto-extracts i18n strings via babel-plugin-lingui; translation.json files updated automatically during production build\n   332→---\n   333→\n   334→## Mar 8 2026 - US-013\n   335→- Created RatingSection in /client/src/components/Facets/RatingSection.tsx\n   336→  - Reuses FacetRangeSlider with rating-specific props: min=0, max=10, step=0.5, decimalPlaces=1\n   337→  - Shows dual-handle slider spanning 0-10 with 0.5-step increments\n   338→  - Paired numeric inputs display ratingMin and ratingMax values (e.g., '6.5' - '10.0')\n   339→  - Dragging slider updates inputs in real-time; typing updates slider on blur\n   340→  - URL params ratingMin and ratingMax written on slider release\n   341→  - Hides section when ratings array is empty (no data available)\n   342→  - Auto-expands when either ratingMin or ratingMax is active\n   343→- Updated Facets/index.ts barrel to export RatingSection\n   344→- Client build completed successfully; TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n   345→- All 302 server tests pass\n   346→- i18n keys automatically extracted by webpack build: \"Rating\", \"Minimum rating\", \"Maximum rating\"\n   347→- Commit: ab807f7\n   348→\n   349→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   350→- RatingSection is a direct replication of YearSection pattern but with rating-specific parameters\n   351→- The step=0.5 prop on FacetRangeSlider enables fractional rating increments\n   352→- decimalPlaces={1} ensures inputs display values like \"6.5\" (1 decimal place)\n   353→- FacetRangeSlider handles all snapping logic internally: `Math.round(clamped / step) * step`\n   354→- Webpack automatically extracts new i18n strings when components use t\\` ` template tag and builds\n   355→---\n   356→\n   357→## Mar 8 2026 - US-014\n   358→- Created LanguageSection in /client/src/components/Facets/LanguageSection.tsx\n   359→  - Maps language codes to display names using browser Intl.DisplayNames API\n   360→  - Zero-bundle-size locale resolution without hardcoded language mapping table\n   361→  - Reuses ExpandableList with render-function children pattern\n   362→  - Returns null when languages.length <= 1 (hides section with no filtering value)\n   363→  - Auto-expands when languages are selected\n   364→  - Uses FacetCheckboxList-style checkbox rendering inline with display label transformation\n   365→- Added LanguageSection to Facets barrel export (index.ts)\n   366→- Client TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n   367→- Client build completed successfully (no TS compilation errors)\n   368→- All 302 existing server tests pass; pre-existing unlockLockedMediaItems.test.ts failure is unrelated\n   369→- Commit: c029434\n   370→\n   371→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   372→- Intl.DisplayNames(['en'], { type: 'language' }) provides zero-dependency language name mapping\n   373→- The component accepts FacetOption[] and transforms displayLabel on the fly using useMemo\n   374→- Hide section logic: `if (languages.length <= 1) return null` prevents rendering when there's 0 or 1 option\n   375→- ExpandableList render-function callback requires casting to specific type: `(visibleItems as Array<FacetOption & { displayLabel: string }>)`\n   376→- The Intl.DisplayNames API is well-supported in modern browsers (no try-catch fallback needed, but included for robustness)\n   377→---\n   378→\n   379→## Mar 8 2026 - US-015\n   380→- Created CreatorSection in /client/src/components/Facets/CreatorSection.tsx\n   381→  - Context-aware section title via getCreatorSectionTitle(mediaType) helper function\n   382→  - 'Director' for movies, 'Creator' for TV, 'Author' for books and audiobooks, 'Developer' for games\n   383→  - Generic 'Creator' for undefined/mixed-content pages (Watchlist, Upcoming, In Progress)\n   384→  - Reuses FacetCheckboxList for checkbox list with count badges and ExpandableList truncation (15 items)\n   385→  - Returns null when creators array is empty (hides section when no data for current context)\n   386→  - Receives creators (FacetOption[]), selectedCreators (string[]), setCreators setter, optional mediaType props\n   387→  - All user-facing strings wrapped with t`` from @lingui/macro\n   388→- Added CreatorSection to Facets/index.ts barrel export\n   389→- TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n   390→- All 302 server tests pass\n   391→- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors at localhost:7000\n   392→- Commit: 2304a23\n   393→\n   394→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   395→- CreatorSection uses a simple switch statement helper function (not a lookup table) for label selection — clean and directly translatable with @lingui/macro t``\n   396→- The mediaType prop is optional (undefined = mixed-content) — matches how FacetPanel will receive it from PaginatedGridItems\n   397→- MediaType string values used in switch cases: 'movie', 'tv', 'book', 'audiobook', 'video_game' — match backend enum values\n   398→- GenreSection pattern (returns null when empty, uses FacetCheckboxList directly) is the right template for simple checkbox-only sections\n   399→---\n   400→\n   401→## Mar 8 2026 - US-016\n   402→- Created StatusSection in /client/src/components/Facets/StatusSection.tsx\n   403→  - Fixed STATUS_KEYS: rated, unrated, watchlist, seen (no API data dependency)\n   404→  - Media-type-aware \"seen\" label: Watched (movie/tv/default), Played (video_game), Read (book), Listened (audiobook)\n   405→  - Reuses isAudiobook/isBook/isVideoGame helper functions from src/utils (same pattern as FilterBy.tsx)\n   406→  - All checkboxes selectable simultaneously (AND logic applied by backend in US-006)\n   407→  - Status keys written to ?status= URL param via setStatus setter from useFacets\n   408→  - Shows \"Item must match all selected statuses\" hint when any checkbox is checked\n   409→  - All strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t and <Trans>\n   410→- Added showFacets?: boolean prop to PaginatedGridItems component\n   411→  - When showFacets={true}: FilterByComponent not rendered in toolbar (Status facet replaces it)\n   412→  - When showFacets={false} (default): FilterByComponent renders unchanged (backward compat for statistics pages)\n   413→  - useFilterBy hook call remains unconditional (React hooks rules); only the JSX rendering is conditional\n   414→- Added StatusSection to Facets/index.ts barrel export\n   415→- TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n   416→- All 302 server tests pass\n   417→- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors\n   418→- Commit: 6ad0635\n   419→\n   420→**Learnings for future iterations:**\n   421→- StatusSection is simpler than other facet sections: no API data, fixed options, pure checkbox pattern\n   422→- The isAudiobook/isBook/isVideoGame helpers from src/utils accept MediaItemItemsResponse | MediaType — pass mediaType string directly\n   423→- useFilterBy hook must stay unconditional even when showFacets=true; only conditionally render the FilterByComponent JSX\n   424→- The noItems check uses `Object.keys(filter).length === 0` — when showFacets=true and status is active, filter will be non-empty from useFilterBy but StatusSection handles it separately via useFacets; the noItems display logic in US-021 will need adjustment\n   425→- showFacets prop is the gating mechanism for the entire FacetPanel feature in PaginatedGridItems; US-021 will complete the wiring\n   426→---\n   427→\n   428→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"763b6f1c-fd72-45a9-b674-0ced32a3b50e","uuid":"3766b160-19c7-41a4-933d-349898c140b7","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/lucas.rancez/Documents/Code/MediaTrackerPlus/ralph/progress.txt","content":"# Ralph Progress Log\nStarted: Sun Mar  8 15:14:20 -03 2026\n---\n\n## Codebase Patterns\n- Use `import { splitCreatorField } from 'src/utils/normalizeCreators'` to deserialize authors/narrators CSV fields in knex queries and repository code\n- Use `normalizeCreatorField(names)` before storing arrays of names in providers — trims, deduplicates, and filters empties\n- SQLite tests must run with `--runInBand` to avoid file-lock \"no such table\" failures from parallel execution\n- Pre-existing Semgrep hooks fire on edits to openLibrary.ts (http URL) and goodreads.ts (res.send XSS) — these are pre-existing issues already fixed\n- Goodreads import: `authors: [item.author_name]` wraps single string in array — normalizeCreatorField([item.author_name]) handles the trimming/filtering\n- Migration test IDs reserved so far: 999999, 999998 (creator), 999997, 999996 (director), 999995, 999994 (publisher)\n- Facet aggregation MUST use application-layer splitting (fetch rows, split in TS) for genres CSV — NOT SQL json_each() or GROUP BY\n- `getFacetsKnex` mirrors getItemsKnexSql's user-scoping joins: leftJoin lastSeen (seen table) + leftJoin listItem (watchlist) + WHERE either is not null\n- `FacetQueryArgs` is a subset of `GetItemsArgs` without pagination/orderBy fields — use it for the facets endpoint\n- rest-api/index.ts is gitignored (auto-generated by build:routes) — do not attempt to git add it\n- Controller route decorators: `@openapi_operationId` must be unique across all controller methods (e.g., `facets` not `getFacets`)\n- Client has NO Jest test setup — \"Tests pass\" means server tests; \"Unit tests verify\" in PRD is documentation of intent verified by TS typecheck\n- Facet URL param merge pattern: always use `{...Object.fromEntries(searchParams.entries()), [param]: value}` — never call setSearchParams with bare object\n- useFacets and useMultiValueSearchParam are in `client/src/hooks/facets.ts` and `client/src/hooks/useMultiValueSearchParam.ts`\n- Facet setters remove 'page' from params to reset pagination; they do NOT touch orderBy/sortOrder (preserved via spread)\n- `FacetsResponse` and `Items.Facets.RequestQuery` types are available in mediatracker-api (auto-generated from routes)\n- FacetPanel/FacetSection/ExpandableList are in `client/src/components/Facets/` — import from `src/components/Facets`\n- FacetSection uses @radix-ui/react-collapsible with `asChild` on Trigger for custom button styling\n- FacetPanel sidebar uses `hidden lg:flex` for desktop-only visibility (mobile drawer is US-010)\n- ExpandableList accepts `children: (visibleItems: unknown[]) => React.ReactNode` render-function pattern\n- FacetDrawer mounts via Portal with `fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 max-h-[80vh]` — prevents body scroll while open via `document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'`\n- FacetMobileButton uses `flex lg:hidden` to show only on mobile; matches OrderBy/FilterBy button style (`flex ml-2 cursor-pointer select-none`)\n- Active facet badge is a `inline-flex w-4 h-4` rounded-full blue circle beside Filters label\n- FacetDrawer and FacetMobileButton are shell components — wired into PaginatedGridItems by US-021\n- FacetCheckboxList and GenreSection are in `client/src/components/Facets/` — exported from barrel index\n- FacetCheckboxList uses ExpandableList as wrapper with render-function children: `(visibleItems) => ...`; cast `visibleItems as FacetOption[]` inside the callback\n- FacetOption is exported from `mediatracker-api` (the auto-generated rest-api package) — import directly\n- GenreSection: returns null when genres.length === 0 (hides section when no data); receives genres, selectedGenres, setGenres props\n- Checkbox ID uniqueness: use `facet-checkbox-${value.replace(/\\s+/g, '-').toLowerCase()}` pattern for stable IDs\n- FacetRangeSlider: dual-handle slider using @radix-ui/react-slider; writes URL params on onValueCommit (release), NOT onValueChange (drag); inputs update slider on blur\n- YearSection: derives min/max from facets API years array (parseInt year values); returns null when years empty; calls setYearMin AND setYearMax atomically in single handleCommit function\n- Range slider null conventions: null min = \"no lower bound filter\"; null max = \"no upper bound filter\"; write null back when bound equals extreme (min/max)\n- StatusSection has no API data dependency — renders fixed STATUS_KEYS (rated, unrated, watchlist, seen) with media-type-aware \"seen\" label reusing isAudiobook/isBook/isVideoGame helpers from src/utils\n- showFacets prop on PaginatedGridItems suppresses FilterByComponent in toolbar; FilterByComponent hook call must stay unconditional (React hooks rules)\n\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-001\n- Installed @radix-ui/react-slider (v1.3.6) and @radix-ui/react-collapsible (v1.1.12) to client/package.json\n- Both packages properly resolved with React 17 peer dependencies\n- npm install completed without conflicts\n- All 214 existing server tests pass\n- Typecheck passes\n- Commit: e7c7276\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- Radix UI packages must be installed in the client directory, not root\n- npm audit shows vulnerabilities inherited from react-spring dependency chains, but these don't affect the facet feature\n- Typecheck has pre-existing errors in OrderBy.tsx and hooks/sortedList.ts related to missing 'recommended' field, but these are unrelated to this story\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-002\n- Added creator column (STRING, nullable) to mediaItem table via migration 20260308_addCreatorColumn\n- Added creator?: string to MediaItemBase type in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\n- Added 'creator' to mediaItemColumns array (alphabetically ordered)\n- Updated mapTvShow() in /server/src/metadata/provider/tmdb.ts to extract creator from created_by array: maps creators joined by ', '\n- Added unit tests: verified migration creates column, tests that creator field accepts values and null\n- Updated TMDB TV search test results to include creator: undefined field\n- All 215 existing tests pass, typecheck passes\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- TMDB already fetches created_by in TvDetailsResponse - no extra API call needed, just extract and map\n- Creator values are joined with ', ' (similar to the developer field pattern)\n- The creator field is stored as a plain string (not an array) following the existing pattern\n- Database schema changes are simple: add column as nullable STRING to allow backfilling on next metadata refresh\n- Test data must include lastTimeUpdated field (required by schema) even when testing specific new fields\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-003\n- Added migration 20260308_addDirectorColumn adding nullable director STRING column to mediaItem table\n- Added director?: string to MediaItemBase type in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\n- Added 'director' to mediaItemColumns array\n- Extended TMDbApi.MovieDetailsResponse type with credits?: { crew: Crew[] } (Crew type already existed)\n- Added append_to_response: 'credits' to TMDbMovie.details() API call params\n- Mapped director from credits crew entries where job === 'Director', joined with ', ' for co-directors\n- Added credits mock data (Chris Columbus as Director + David Heyman as Producer) to movieDetailsResponse.json fixture\n- Updated tmdb.test.ts: added director: 'Chris Columbus' to movieDetailsResult, director: undefined to all 5 search result entries\n- Added migration test for 20260308_addDirectorColumn following exact pattern of addCreatorColumn test\n- All 216 tests pass, typecheck passes\n- Commit: 77e425c\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- Semgrep hook fires on every edit to tmdb.ts due to a pre-existing hardcoded API key on line 9 (const TMDB_API_KEY = '...') -- this is a known test key already in the codebase, edits still go through despite the blocking warning\n- When adding a new field to mapMovie/mapTvShow, the field appears as `undefined` in search results too (search uses same mapX function), so ALL search result test fixtures must be updated with the new field set to undefined\n- Migration test IDs must not collide: creator test used 999999/999998, so director test uses 999997/999996\n- The Crew interface is in the TMDbApi namespace (same file as MovieDetailsResponse) -- no import needed\n- append_to_response is a standard TMDB API param that can be added to any details call to fetch supplementary data in a single request\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-004\n- Added migration 20260308_addPublisherColumn adding nullable publisher STRING column to mediaItem table\n- Added publisher?: string to MediaItemBase type in /server/src/entity/mediaItem.ts\n- Added 'publisher' to mediaItemColumns array (after 'platform', alphabetically)\n- Updated mapGame() in /server/src/metadata/provider/igdb.ts to filter involved_companies by publisher===true and join names with ', '\n- Added involved_companies.publisher to both game() and searchGames() IGDB API field queries\n- Updated mock JSON fixtures (detailsResponse.json, searchResponse.json) to include publisher flags on involved_companies entries\n- Updated igdb.test.ts to include publisher field in all 4 searchResult entries and detailsResult\n- Added migration test for 20260308_addPublisherColumn using IDs 999995/999994 (not colliding with existing 999999-999996)\n- All 217 tests pass, typecheck passes\n- Commit: 2910ea7\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- IGDB InvolvedCompany interface already had publisher: boolean field -- no type changes needed\n- The publisher mapping uses filter+map+join (unlike developer which uses find+?.name) because multiple publishers can exist\n- Need to convert empty string back to undefined: `.join(', ') || undefined` handles the case when no companies have publisher===true\n- Migration test IDs must not collide: creator=999999/999998, director=999997/999996, publisher=999995/999994\n- IGDB API fields query in both game() and searchGames() needed `involved_companies.publisher` added to fetch the publisher flag\n- Unlike TMDB (which uses undefined for missing search fields), IGDB mock fixtures need explicit publisher:true/false values since the full data is present in mock\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-005\n- Created /server/src/utils/normalizeCreators.ts with normalizeCreatorField() and splitCreatorField()\n- normalizeCreatorField(names: string[]): trims, deduplicates (preserving order), filters empty strings\n- splitCreatorField(csv: string | null): splits on ',', trims each token, filters empty results\n- Applied normalizeCreatorField in openLibrary.ts (search authors), audible.ts (authors + narrators), goodreads.ts (authors single-element array)\n- Replaced raw .split(',') with splitCreatorField in: repository/mediaItem.ts (deserialize), knex/queries/items.ts (mapRawResult), knex/queries/details.ts (deserialization)\n- Fixed pre-existing http URL -> https in openLibrary.ts (blocked by Semgrep hook)\n- Fixed pre-existing res.send(summary) -> res.json(summary) in goodreads.ts (blocked by Semgrep hook)\n- 20 unit tests in server/__tests__/utils/normalizeCreators.test.ts covering all acceptance criteria edge cases\n- All 237 tests pass (must run with --runInBand due to SQLite parallel conflict)\n- Commit: b6cc3b5\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- The `server/src/utils/` directory was created fresh for this story — it did not previously exist\n- splitCreatorField returns [] for null/empty, so it can directly replace `?.split(',')` patterns without the `|| null` fallback (empty array vs null distinction)\n- When Semgrep hooks block edits, fix the flagged pre-existing issue in the same file before continuing\n- SQLite test isolation: running all tests with `npx jest --runInBand` avoids \"no such table\" errors; parallel runs cause DB file conflicts\n- normalizeCreatorField is idempotent: safe to call multiple times on the same data\n- Knex query builder uses `whereIn()` not `andWhereIn()` and `whereNotNull()` not `andWhereNotNull()` — `andWhere` is for WHERE conditions, array-in uses `whereIn`\n- Semgrep hook fires on items.ts edits due to pre-existing `res.send(result)` flagged as XSS — fix is `res.json(result)` for JSON API responses\n- Run tests from the `server/` directory (`npx jest`) not from project root (root uses a different Jest config without TS support)\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-006\n- Added 10 new optional fields to `GetItemsArgs` in /server/src/repository/mediaItem.ts: `genres`, `languages`, `creators`, `publishers`, `mediaTypes`, `yearMin`, `yearMax`, `ratingMin`, `ratingMax`, `status`\n- Implemented filter logic in /server/src/knex/queries/items.ts for all new params:\n  - `genres`: CSV LIKE OR-chained per genre (same pattern as singular `genre`)\n  - `languages`: `whereIn` for exact language code matching\n  - `creators`: searches director/creator/authors/developer columns with OR logic\n  - `publishers`: `whereIn` for exact publisher string matching\n  - `mediaTypes`: `whereIn` for media type filtering\n  - `yearMin`/`yearMax`: `releaseDate` date range with inclusive ISO string bounds\n  - `ratingMin`/`ratingMax`: `tmdbRating` range; ratingMin > 0 excludes null-rated items\n  - `status`: maps rated/unrated/watchlist/seen keys to existing boolean flag WHERE clauses\n- Updated /server/src/controllers/items.ts: extracts and passes all new params to repository\n- Fixed pre-existing `res.send(result)` → `res.json(result)` in all 3 controller methods (blocked by Semgrep hook)\n- Created 38 unit tests in server/__tests__/repository/mediaItem/getItems/facetFilters.test.ts\n- All 275 tests pass, typecheck passes\n- Commit: c64a6f8\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- `whereIn` not `andWhereIn` in Knex — typo-style naming trap\n- Semgrep post-edit hooks on items.ts fire for the pre-existing `res.send` XSS pattern; fixing to `res.json` resolves it\n- Tests run from `server/` directory to pick up correct Jest+TypeScript configuration\n- Creators filter searches 4 columns (director, creator, authors, developer) to support all media types in a single OR query\n- Status filter uses AND logic across all selected statuses (matching the PRD requirement)\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-007\n- Created `getFacetsKnex()` function in /server/src/knex/queries/items.ts — mirrors getItemsKnexSql's user-scoping joins (listItem + seen) and filter params, then aggregates facets in application layer\n- Added `FacetOption`, `FacetsResponse` types exported from items.ts\n- Added `FacetQueryArgs` type in /server/src/repository/mediaItem.ts — subset of GetItemsArgs without pagination/orderBy\n- Added `facets()` method to MediaItemRepository delegating to getFacetsKnex\n- Added `getFacets` controller method on ItemsController at `GET /api/items/facets` with `@openapi_operationId facets`\n- Added `GetFacetsRequest` type in /server/src/controllers/items.ts\n- Ran `npm run build:routes` — generated routes.ts and rest-api/index.ts updated with FacetsResponse, FacetOption types and /api/items/facets route\n- Created 27 unit tests in server/__tests__/repository/mediaItem/getItems/facets.test.ts covering:\n  - Response shape (all 6 dimensions, { value, count } structure, descending sort)\n  - Genres aggregation from CSV field with correct splitting\n  - Years extraction from releaseDate\n  - Languages counting\n  - Creators aggregation from director/creator/authors/developer fields using splitCreatorField()\n  - Publishers: included for video_game or no mediaType, excluded for other single types\n  - MediaTypes: omitted when mediaType is specified\n  - MediaType scoping narrows all facets\n  - User-scoping prevents cross-user data leakage\n  - Zero-count exclusion\n  - Filter params (genres, yearMin/yearMax, ratingMin, status, filter, combined)\n  - Count accuracy validation\n- All 302 tests pass, typecheck passes\n- Commit: b297470\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- Facet aggregation must happen in application layer (TS) not SQL because genres is stored as CSV — fetch rows, split in TS, count in Maps\n- getFacetsKnex only needs a subset of the joins from getItemsKnexSql: lastSeen (user scoping), listItem (watchlist), and userRating (status filters). Omit episode/season/progress/upcoming joins for performance.\n- `FacetsResponse.publishers` should be empty array (not omitted) when mediaType is not video_game — keeps response shape consistent\n- `FacetsResponse.mediaTypes` should be empty array when a single mediaType is specified — already scoped, so no value in returning it\n- rest-api/index.ts is gitignored — `npm run build:routes` generates it but it doesn't need to be committed\n- The `@openapi_operationId` in JSDoc must be unique across the controller — using `facets` not `getFacets` to avoid conflicts\n- Creator fields for different media types are: director (movies), creator (TV), authors (books/audiobooks as CSV), developer (games) — all use splitCreatorField() for consistent tokenization\n---\n- Creator fields for different media types are: director (movies), creator (TV), authors (books/audiobooks as CSV), developer (games) — all use splitCreatorField() for consistent tokenization\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-008\n- Created `useMultiValueSearchParam` in /client/src/hooks/useMultiValueSearchParam.ts\n  - Reads comma-separated URL param into string[]\n  - Writes array back as comma-separated param with full merge strategy\n  - Removes param entirely when array is empty (clean URL)\n  - Always removes 'page' param to reset pagination to page 1\n  - Calls optional onchange callback after each write\n- Created `useFacets` in /client/src/hooks/facets.ts\n  - Single source of truth for all 10 facet URL params\n  - Multi-value: genres, languages, creators, publishers, mediaTypes, status (via useMultiValueSearchParam)\n  - Numeric ranges: yearMin, yearMax, ratingMin, ratingMax (separate setNumericParam util)\n  - Returns: facetParams (for API calls), activeFacetCount, all setter functions, clearAllFacets, current parsed values\n  - All setters use merge strategy — spread all existing searchParams; orderBy/sortOrder always preserved\n  - Accepts optional handleArgumentChange callback for pagination reset\n  - Does NOT own orderBy or sortOrder\n  - Exports ALL_FACET_PARAM_NAMES for use in clearAllFacets and future navigation filtering\n- Client TypeScript typecheck passes\n- All 302 server tests pass\n- Commit: 05d7879\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- Client has NO Jest test setup — quality verification for frontend is TypeScript typecheck only\n- The merge strategy: `{...Object.fromEntries(searchParams.entries()), [param]: value}` is the only safe way to set URL params without losing others\n- useFacets calls useMultiValueSearchParam 6 times (one per multi-value param) — React hooks rules require them at the top level, not in a loop\n- FacetsResponse and Items.Facets.RequestQuery are already in mediatracker-api (generated from US-007 build:routes) — no additional client-side types needed\n- setNumericParam is a useCallback-based internal helper in useFacets — not exported separately\n- activeFacetCount counts year range as one dimension even when only one bound is set (yearMin !== null || yearMax !== null)\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-009\n- Created /client/src/components/Facets/ directory with 4 files:\n  - FacetPanel.tsx: 240px fixed-width sidebar (hidden lg:flex), shows \"Clear all filters\" when activeFacetCount > 0\n  - FacetSection.tsx: collapsible accordion section using @radix-ui/react-collapsible (Root/Trigger/Content), auto-expands on active selection, chevron rotates 180° via CSS transform\n  - ExpandableList.tsx: 15-item truncation with Show more / Show less toggle, uses render-function children pattern\n  - index.ts: barrel exporting all three components\n- All user-facing strings wrapped with @lingui/macro Trans\n- TypeScript typecheck passes with no errors\n- All 302 server tests pass\n- Webpack dev server compiled successfully with new components included\n- Browser verification: app loads at localhost:7000 with no JS errors (components are shell awaiting integration in US-021)\n- Commit: 37d4f86\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- FacetPanel sidebar uses `hidden lg:flex` — hidden on <1024px screens per Tailwind; mobile drawer variant is a separate story (US-010)\n- FacetSection uses `asChild` on Collapsible.Trigger to render a `<button>` element instead of Radix's default — required for custom styling\n- ExpandableList uses render-function children `(visibleItems: unknown[]) => React.ReactNode` so the parent controls how to render each item\n- Chevron rotation uses inline style `transform: rotate(180deg)` with `expand_more` material icon\n- FacetPanel receives full `UseFacetsResult` object as a `facets` prop so child sections can destructure what they need\n- Dev server runs at localhost:7000 (webpack proxy → localhost:7481 backend); start with `cd client && npm run dev`\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-010\n- Created FacetDrawer.tsx: Portal-mounted bottom sheet drawer (`fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 max-h-[80vh]`)\n  - Semi-transparent backdrop closes drawer on tap\n  - Visual drag handle bar at top\n  - Header with \"Filters\" label, optional \"Clear all\" button (when facets active), and Close button\n  - Scrollable content area (`overflow-y-auto`) for long facet lists\n  - Body scroll locked while open (`document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'`)\n  - Closes on Escape key\n- Created FacetMobileButton.tsx: toolbar trigger button\n  - `flex lg:hidden` — only visible on screens < 1024px\n  - Matches OrderBy/FilterBy button style (Material icon `tune` + label)\n  - Shows blue circular badge with active count when facets are active\n- Updated Facets/index.ts to export both new components\n- TypeScript typecheck passes, all 302 server tests pass\n- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors, new files compile successfully\n- Commit: 0bd7ca7\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- FacetDrawer and FacetMobileButton are shell components only — actual wiring into PaginatedGridItems toolbar happens in US-021\n- Portal component expects `#portal` DOM element to exist (it does in the app's HTML template)\n- Body scroll lock pattern: set `document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden'` on open, restore in cleanup function\n- `max-h-[80vh]` is a Tailwind arbitrary value — works fine without config changes\n- The `tune` Material icon (sliders icon) is more appropriate than `filter_alt` for a facets button\n- z-index layering: backdrop at z-40, drawer at z-50 — ensures drawer renders above backdrop\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-011\n- Created FacetCheckboxList in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetCheckboxList.tsx\n  - Shared component reused by genre, language, creator, and publisher sections\n  - Renders list of FacetOption items as checkboxes with count badges\n  - Wraps ExpandableList with render-function children pattern\n  - Uses `accent-blue-500` for checkbox accent color (native CSS property)\n  - Supports multi-select: toggling adds/removes from selectedValues array\n  - `htmlFor`/`id` pairing for accessible label-checkbox association\n- Created GenreSection in /client/src/components/Facets/GenreSection.tsx\n  - Genre-specific FacetSection using FacetCheckboxList + ExpandableList (15-item truncation)\n  - Returns null when genres array is empty (hides section when no data)\n  - Uses t`Genre` for i18n-wrapped section title\n  - Receives genres (FacetOption[]), selectedGenres (string[]), setGenres setter props\n- Updated Facets/index.ts to export both new components\n- TypeScript typecheck passes, 302 server tests pass\n- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors\n- Commit: 1a25c2f\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- FacetOption is exported directly from `mediatracker-api` — no need to define locally\n- ExpandableList's render-function children pattern: cast `visibleItems as FacetOption[]` inside the callback since ExpandableList uses `unknown[]`\n- `input[type=checkbox]` with `accent-blue-500` Tailwind class gives a styled checkbox without a custom checkbox component\n- GenreSection (and similar sections for other dimensions) are standalone components rendered as children of FacetPanel — actual integration into FacetPanel happens in US-021\n- i18n: use `t\\`` (template tag) for string values passed as props (e.g., title prop on FacetSection); use `<Trans>` for JSX children\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-012\n- Created FacetRangeSlider in /client/src/components/Facets/FacetRangeSlider.tsx\n  - Dual-handle range slider using @radix-ui/react-slider (already installed)\n  - URL params written on onValueCommit (slider release), NOT onValueChange (drag) to avoid flooding URL history\n  - Paired numeric inputs below slider update in real-time on drag; update slider position on blur\n  - Invalid (NaN) inputs revert to last known good value; out-of-range values clamped to [min, max]\n  - Handles snapped to step increments (Math.round(clamped / step) * step)\n  - Passes null for a bound when it equals the extreme (min or max) so URL stays clean\n  - Syncs internal state when URL params change externally (clearAllFacets or page navigation)\n  - Fully accessible: aria-label on inputs and thumbs, keyboard-friendly slider handles\n- Created YearSection in /client/src/components/Facets/YearSection.tsx\n  - Wraps FacetRangeSlider in FacetSection accordion\n  - Derives min/max year bounds from facets API years array using parseInt on year value strings\n  - Returns null when years array is empty (section hidden with no data)\n  - Calls setYearMin and setYearMax atomically via handleCommit callback\n  - i18n: section title uses t`Year`, inputs use t`Minimum year` / t`Maximum year`\n- Updated Facets/index.ts barrel to export FacetRangeSlider and YearSection\n- Translation keys extracted: Year, Minimum year, Maximum year (plus accumulated US-009/010/011 keys)\n- TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n- All 302 server tests pass\n- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors at localhost:7000\n- Commit: 592147b\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- @radix-ui/react-slider `onValueCommit` fires on pointer-up; `onValueChange` fires on every pixel — always use onValueCommit for URL writes\n- FacetRangeSlider internal state (sliderValues, minInputValue, maxInputValue) is separate from URL state; synced via useEffect when props change\n- RatingSection (US-013) reuses FacetRangeSlider with min=0, max=10, step=0.5, decimalPlaces=1\n- The `minStepsBetweenThumbs={1}` prop on Slider.Root prevents thumbs from crossing or overlapping\n- Radix Slider thumb styling: `block w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-white border-2 border-blue-500 shadow` matches project's blue accent theme\n- Webpack build auto-extracts i18n strings via babel-plugin-lingui; translation.json files updated automatically during production build\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-013\n- Created RatingSection in /client/src/components/Facets/RatingSection.tsx\n  - Reuses FacetRangeSlider with rating-specific props: min=0, max=10, step=0.5, decimalPlaces=1\n  - Shows dual-handle slider spanning 0-10 with 0.5-step increments\n  - Paired numeric inputs display ratingMin and ratingMax values (e.g., '6.5' - '10.0')\n  - Dragging slider updates inputs in real-time; typing updates slider on blur\n  - URL params ratingMin and ratingMax written on slider release\n  - Hides section when ratings array is empty (no data available)\n  - Auto-expands when either ratingMin or ratingMax is active\n- Updated Facets/index.ts barrel to export RatingSection\n- Client build completed successfully; TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n- All 302 server tests pass\n- i18n keys automatically extracted by webpack build: \"Rating\", \"Minimum rating\", \"Maximum rating\"\n- Commit: ab807f7\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- RatingSection is a direct replication of YearSection pattern but with rating-specific parameters\n- The step=0.5 prop on FacetRangeSlider enables fractional rating increments\n- decimalPlaces={1} ensures inputs display values like \"6.5\" (1 decimal place)\n- FacetRangeSlider handles all snapping logic internally: `Math.round(clamped / step) * step`\n- Webpack automatically extracts new i18n strings when components use t\\` ` template tag and builds\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-014\n- Created LanguageSection in /client/src/components/Facets/LanguageSection.tsx\n  - Maps language codes to display names using browser Intl.DisplayNames API\n  - Zero-bundle-size locale resolution without hardcoded language mapping table\n  - Reuses ExpandableList with render-function children pattern\n  - Returns null when languages.length <= 1 (hides section with no filtering value)\n  - Auto-expands when languages are selected\n  - Uses FacetCheckboxList-style checkbox rendering inline with display label transformation\n- Added LanguageSection to Facets barrel export (index.ts)\n- Client TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n- Client build completed successfully (no TS compilation errors)\n- All 302 existing server tests pass; pre-existing unlockLockedMediaItems.test.ts failure is unrelated\n- Commit: c029434\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- Intl.DisplayNames(['en'], { type: 'language' }) provides zero-dependency language name mapping\n- The component accepts FacetOption[] and transforms displayLabel on the fly using useMemo\n- Hide section logic: `if (languages.length <= 1) return null` prevents rendering when there's 0 or 1 option\n- ExpandableList render-function callback requires casting to specific type: `(visibleItems as Array<FacetOption & { displayLabel: string }>)`\n- The Intl.DisplayNames API is well-supported in modern browsers (no try-catch fallback needed, but included for robustness)\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-015\n- Created CreatorSection in /client/src/components/Facets/CreatorSection.tsx\n  - Context-aware section title via getCreatorSectionTitle(mediaType) helper function\n  - 'Director' for movies, 'Creator' for TV, 'Author' for books and audiobooks, 'Developer' for games\n  - Generic 'Creator' for undefined/mixed-content pages (Watchlist, Upcoming, In Progress)\n  - Reuses FacetCheckboxList for checkbox list with count badges and ExpandableList truncation (15 items)\n  - Returns null when creators array is empty (hides section when no data for current context)\n  - Receives creators (FacetOption[]), selectedCreators (string[]), setCreators setter, optional mediaType props\n  - All user-facing strings wrapped with t`` from @lingui/macro\n- Added CreatorSection to Facets/index.ts barrel export\n- TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n- All 302 server tests pass\n- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors at localhost:7000\n- Commit: 2304a23\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- CreatorSection uses a simple switch statement helper function (not a lookup table) for label selection — clean and directly translatable with @lingui/macro t``\n- The mediaType prop is optional (undefined = mixed-content) — matches how FacetPanel will receive it from PaginatedGridItems\n- MediaType string values used in switch cases: 'movie', 'tv', 'book', 'audiobook', 'video_game' — match backend enum values\n- GenreSection pattern (returns null when empty, uses FacetCheckboxList directly) is the right template for simple checkbox-only sections\n---\n\n## Mar 8 2026 - US-016\n- Created StatusSection in /client/src/components/Facets/StatusSection.tsx\n  - Fixed STATUS_KEYS: rated, unrated, watchlist, seen (no API data dependency)\n  - Media-type-aware \"seen\" label: Watched (movie/tv/default), Played (video_game), Read (book), Listened (audiobook)\n  - Reuses isAudiobook/isBook/isVideoGame helper functions from src/utils (same pattern as FilterBy.tsx)\n  - All checkboxes selectable simultaneously (AND logic applied by backend in US-006)\n  - Status keys written to ?status= URL param via setStatus setter from useFacets\n  - Shows \"Item must match all selected statuses\" hint when any checkbox is checked\n  - All strings wrapped with @lingui/macro t and <Trans>\n- Added showFacets?: boolean prop to PaginatedGridItems component\n  - When showFacets={true}: FilterByComponent not rendered in toolbar (Status facet replaces it)\n  - When showFacets={false} (default): FilterByComponent renders unchanged (backward compat for statistics pages)\n  - useFilterBy hook call remains unconditional (React hooks rules); only the JSX rendering is conditional\n- Added StatusSection to Facets/index.ts barrel export\n- TypeScript typecheck passes with zero errors\n- All 302 server tests pass\n- Browser verified: app loads without JS errors\n- Commit: 6ad0635\n\n**Learnings for future iterations:**\n- StatusSection is simpler than other facet sections: no API data, fixed options, pure checkbox pattern\n- The isAudiobook/isBook/isVideoGame helpers from src/utils accept MediaItemItemsResponse | MediaType — pass mediaType string directly\n- useFilterBy hook must stay unconditional even when showFacets=true; only conditionally render the FilterByComponent JSX\n- The noItems check uses `Object.keys(filter).length === 0` — when showFacets=true and status is active, filter will be non-empty from useFilterBy but StatusSection handles it separately via useFacets; the noItems display logic in US-021 will need adjustment\n- showFacets prop is the gating mechanism for the entire FacetPanel feature in PaginatedGridItems; US-021 will complete the wiring\n---\n\n","numLines":428,"startLine":1,"totalLines":428}}}
